0:40:48,606 --> 00:40:51,973\r\n...electricity shall be passed through\r\nyour body until you are dead...\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:40:52,210 --> 00:40:54,440\r\n...in accordance with state law.\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:40:54,879 --> 00:40:57,245\r\nGod have mercy on your soul.\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:40:58,550 --> 00:40:59,983\r\nAmen.\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:41:02,387 --> 00:41:03,513\r\nRoll on two.\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:41:07,559 --> 00:41:09,083\r\nAnd that's that.\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:41:12,029 --> 00:41:15,396\r\nI'm frying! I'm frying!\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:41:17,101 --> 00:41:20,229\r\nI'm a done tom turkey!\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:41:21,905 --> 00:41:24,806\r\nThis is a shocking experience!\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:41:25,476 --> 00:41:28,570\r\nOne of the witnesses\r\nshowed up a day early.\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:41:35,586 --> 00:41:38,316\r\nLet's do it again,\r\nand let's get it right this time.\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:41:38,522 --> 00:41:40,922\r\nGet that idiot out of the chair.\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:42:41,016 --> 00:42:45,646\r\nDo you think if a man sincerely\r\nrepents on what he done wrong...\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:42:46,688 --> 00:42:50,180\r\n...that he might get to go back to\r\nthe time that was happiest for him...\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:42:50,792 --> 00:42:52,555\r\n...and live there forever?\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:42:54,963 --> 00:42:56,988\r\nCould that be what heaven's like?\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:00,994\r\nI just about believe that very thing.\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:43:07,042 --> 00:43:10,341\r\nHad me a young wife when I was 18.\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:43:11,012 --> 00:43:15,676\r\nSpent our first summer in the mountains.\r\nMade love every night.\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:43:16,351 --> 00:43:19,479\r\nAnd she'd lie there after...\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:43:20,422 --> 00:43:22,788\r\n...bare-breasted in the firelight.\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:43:24,058 --> 00:43:27,255\r\nAnd we'd talk sometimes\r\ntill the sun come up.\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:43:30,531 --> 00:43:32,795\r\nThat was my best time.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:43:52,820 --> 00:43:54,481\r\nIt'll be fine.\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:43:55,723 --> 00:43:57,384\r\nYou'll do fine.\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:44:33,493 --> 00:44:37,224\r\nArlen Bitterbuck, electricity shall\r\nnow be passed through your body...\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:44:37,430 --> 00:44:41,491\r\n...until you are dead,\r\nin accordance with state law.\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:44:41,701 --> 00:44:44,101\r\nGod have mercy on your soul.\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:45:03,822 --> 00:45:05,016\r\nRoll on two.\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:45:49,810 --> 00:45:51,334\r\nAgain.\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:45:57,517 --> 00:45:59,212\r\n<i>Adi�s, chief.</i>\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:45:59,586 --> 00:46:04,182\r\nDrop us a card from hell.\r\nLet us know if it's hot enough.\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:46:06,793 --> 00:46:08,920\r\nHe's paid what he owed.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:46:09,329 --> 00:46:11,627\r\nHe's square with the house again...\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:46:11,832 --> 00:46:14,528\r\n...so keep your goddamn hands off him.\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:46:34,687 --> 00:46:36,518\r\nWhat's up his ass?\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:46:36,722 --> 00:46:38,019\r\nYou.\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:46:39,025 --> 00:46:41,619\r\nAlways. You, Percy.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:46:42,228 --> 00:46:45,391\r\nYou gotta hate the new boy?\r\nThat the way it is around here?\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:46:47,366 --> 00:46:50,665\r\nWhy don't you just move on?\r\nTake that job at Briar Ridge?\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:46:51,570 --> 00:46:54,038\r\nOh, yeah. I know all about it.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:46:54,540 --> 00:46:57,839\r\nSounds to me like a pretty good job.\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:46:59,211 --> 00:47:02,669\r\nI might just take it too,\r\nsoon as you put me out front.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:47:03,816 --> 00:47:05,249\r\nYeah, you heard me.\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:47:05,818 --> 00:47:08,445\r\nI want Brutal's spot\r\nfor the next execution.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:47:11,890 --> 00:47:16,293\r\nSeeing a man die, that's not enough.\r\nYou gotta smell his nuts cook.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:47:16,494 --> 00:47:18,928\r\nI just wanna be out front, is all.\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:47:20,231 --> 00:47:22,199\r\nCome on. One time.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:47:23,435 --> 00:47:24,902\r\nAnd then you know what?\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:47:25,103 --> 00:47:28,038\r\nYou'll be rid of me. I swear.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:47:28,239 --> 00:47:30,070\r\nAnd if I say no?\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:47:31,276 --> 00:47:34,734\r\nWell, I might just stick around\r\nfor good.\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:47:35,580 --> 00:47:37,480\r\nMake me a career of this...\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:47:38,783 --> 00:47:40,114\r\n...boss.\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:48:32,936 --> 00:48:35,131\r\nYou are not gonna believe this.\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:48:44,714 --> 00:48:46,045\r\nLook.\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:48:47,650 --> 00:48:50,141\r\nI done tame me that mouse.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:48:51,154 --> 00:48:52,553\r\nWe see that.\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:48:54,157 --> 00:48:57,593\r\nWatch this. Watch what he do.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:49:04,667 --> 00:49:06,601\r\nAin't he something, now?\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:49:07,637 --> 00:49:09,798\r\nHe's smart, Mr. Jingles.\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:49:10,006 --> 00:49:12,167\r\n- Mr. Jingles?\r\n- That his name.\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:49:12,575 --> 00:49:14,736\r\nHe whispered in my ear.\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:49:15,278 --> 00:49:16,336\r\nHey, captain...\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:49:16,546 --> 00:49:20,209\r\n...could I have a box for my mouse\r\nso he can sleep in here with me?\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:49:20,416 --> 00:49:23,077\r\nYour English gets better\r\nwhen you want something.\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:49:23,285 --> 00:49:25,219\r\nWanna see what else he can do?\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:49:26,721 --> 00:49:28,188\r\nWatch, watch.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:49:28,390 --> 00:49:31,416\r\nMr. Jingle? Mr. Jingle,\r\nwanna play fetch?\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:49:31,793 --> 00:49:33,226\r\nWanna play fetch?\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:49:34,029 --> 00:49:36,327\r\nPlay fetch. Watch, watch.\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:49:56,151 --> 00:49:59,052\r\nHe fetch it every time. Every time.\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:49:59,221 --> 00:50:03,920\r\nThat's some smart mouse, Del.\r\nLike he a circus mouse or something.\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:50:06,127 --> 00:50:09,289\r\nCorrect. That just what he is too.\r\nHe's a circus mouse.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:50:09,496 --> 00:50:11,521\r\nWhen I get out,\r\nhe'll make me rich.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:50:11,932 --> 00:50:14,264\r\nYou just watch and see\r\nif he don't do that.\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:50:14,568 --> 00:50:16,763\r\nPlay fetch? We play fetch again?\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:50:17,404 --> 00:50:19,235\r\nWell, well, well.\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:50:19,707 --> 00:50:21,902\r\nLooks like you found yourself\r\na new friend.\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:50:22,576 --> 00:50:23,941\r\nDon't hurt him.\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:50:25,479 --> 00:50:27,913\r\n- Okay?\r\n- Is that the one I chased?\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:50:28,315 --> 00:50:29,976\r\nYeah, that's the one.\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:50:30,484 --> 00:50:33,749\r\nOnly Del says his name is Mr. Jingles.\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:50:34,822 --> 00:50:35,880\r\nIs that so?\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:50:37,091 --> 00:50:38,786\r\nDel's been asking for a box.\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:50:39,593 --> 00:50:43,393\r\nThinks the mouse will sleep in it,\r\nI guess. Might keep it for a pet.\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:50:45,766 --> 00:50:47,063\r\nWhat do you think?\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:50:48,302 --> 00:50:52,135\r\nYou know what?\r\nWe ought to find a cigar box...\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:50:52,605 --> 00:50:57,235\r\n...and get some cotton batting\r\nfrom the dispensary to line it with.\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:50:59,545 --> 00:51:02,605\r\nYeah. That should do real nice.\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:51:11,991 --> 00:51:14,459\r\nMan said get a cigar box.\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:51:24,070 --> 00:51:25,537\r\nMorning.\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:51:30,376 --> 00:51:32,401\r\nHal, you wanted to see me?\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:51:32,679 --> 00:51:33,976\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:36,038\r\nClose the door.\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:51:43,322 --> 00:51:45,051\r\nSo you know...\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:51:46,558 --> 00:51:49,049\r\n...you got a new prisoner\r\ncoming in here tomorrow.\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:51:50,162 --> 00:51:51,823\r\n\"William Wharton.\"\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:51:52,564 --> 00:51:54,225\r\nHe's what you call...\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:51:54,533 --> 00:51:56,501\r\n...a problem child.\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:51:57,369 --> 00:52:01,066\r\nGot \"Billy the Kid\" tattooed\r\non his left arm.\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:52:01,273 --> 00:52:05,334\r\nBeen rambling all over the state\r\nlast few years...\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:52:05,777 --> 00:52:07,972\r\n...causing all kinds of trouble.\r\n\r\n538\r\n00:52:08,747 --> 00:52:10,681\r\nFinally hit the big time.\r\n\r\n539\r\n00:52:12,084 --> 00:52:15,383\r\nKilled three people in a holdup.\r\n\r\n540\r\n00:52:15,587 --> 00:52:17,714\r\nOne of them a pregnant woman.\r\n\r\n541\r\n00:52:20,225 --> 00:52:22,215\r\nBad news all around.\r\n\r\n542\r\n00:52:24,228 --> 00:52:25,695\r\nHal?\r\n\r\n543\r\n00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:37,902\r\nIt's a tumor, Paul.\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:52:39,577 --> 00:52:41,306\r\nA brain tumor.\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:52:43,047 --> 00:52:44,708\r\nThey got...\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:52:45,049 --> 00:52:47,142\r\n...x- ray pictures of it.\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:52:48,552 --> 00:52:51,077\r\nIt's the size of a lemon, they said.\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:52:53,791 --> 00:52:55,053\r\nAnd...\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:52:56,227 --> 00:52:57,751\r\n...way down...\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:52:59,597 --> 00:53:01,792\r\n...deep inside,\r\nwhere they can't operate.\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:53:03,834 --> 00:53:05,495\r\nI haven't told her.\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:53:07,270 --> 00:53:09,238\r\nI can't think how.\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:53:13,009 --> 00:53:15,136\r\nFor the life of me, Paul...\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:53:16,646 --> 00:53:19,638\r\n...I can't think how\r\nto tell my wife...\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:53:23,119 --> 00:53:25,087\r\n...she's going to die.\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:54:50,204 --> 00:54:51,831\r\nOh, God.\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:54:52,507 --> 00:54:54,065\r\nOh, God.\r\n\r\n558\r\n00:54:57,945 --> 00:54:59,344\r\nI'm going.\r\n\r\n559\r\n00:54:59,547 --> 00:55:03,540\r\n- What?\r\n- To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.\r\n\r\n560\r\n00:55:03,885 --> 00:55:05,352\r\nToday.\r\n\r\n561\r\n00:55:05,853 --> 00:55:08,788\r\nSoon as we get that new inmate\r\nsquared away.\r\n\r\n562\r\n00:55:08,956 --> 00:55:10,446\r\nThat bad?\r\n\r\n563\r\n00:55:10,858 --> 00:55:12,291\r\nOh, yeah.\r\n\r\n564\r\n00:55:34,381 --> 00:55:36,576\r\nThe boy is doped to the gills.\r\n\r\n565\r\n00:55:39,553 --> 00:55:40,781\r\nHand me them clothes.\r\n\r\n566\r\n00:55:43,823 --> 00:55:45,723\r\nWilliam Wharton?\r\n\r\n567\r\n00:55:46,159 --> 00:55:49,356\r\nHey! You put on these clothes now,\r\nyou hear?\r\n\r\n568\r\n00:55:57,470 --> 00:55:59,563\r\nWe're gonna have to do this.\r\n\r\n569\r\n00:56:00,807 --> 00:56:02,434\r\nHellraiser, huh?\r\n\r\n570\r\n00:56:02,642 --> 00:56:05,167\r\nLook more like a limp noodle to me.\r\n\r\n571\r\n00:56:05,345 --> 00:56:08,438\r\nHey. Hey.\r\n\r\n572\r\n00:56:09,081 --> 00:56:12,881\r\nYou've been declared competent, son.\r\nYou know what that means?\r\n\r\n573\r\n00:56:13,619 --> 00:56:16,315\r\nMeans you're gonna ride the lightning.\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n574\r\n00:56:17,356 --> 00:56:20,052\r\nPercy, could you shut up,\r\ngive us a hand here?\r\n\r\n575\r\n00:56:20,926 --> 00:56:22,621\r\nHellraiser.\r\n\r\n576\r\n00:56:53,591 --> 00:56:55,081\r\nYou don't look so good.\r\n\r\n577\r\n00:56:57,061 --> 00:56:59,029\r\nLook like you're running you a fever.\r\n\r\n578\r\n00:57:04,802 --> 00:57:06,394\r\nBoss Edgecomb?\r\n\r\n579\r\n00:57:07,905 --> 00:57:09,839\r\nI needs to see you down here, boss.\r\n\r\n580\r\n00:57:12,410 --> 00:57:15,902\r\nI got things to tend to just now,\r\nJohn Coffey. You just...\r\n\r\n581\r\n00:57:17,382 --> 00:57:20,749\r\nYou just stay still in your cell.\r\n\r\n582\r\n00:57:32,330 --> 00:57:33,558\r\nE Block.\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:11,290\r\nCome on, let's go.\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:58:12,536 --> 00:58:14,629\r\nCome on. Look alive, big boy.\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:58:29,318 --> 00:58:30,546\r\nCareful.\r\n\r\n586\r\n00:58:34,056 --> 00:58:37,219\r\n- Careful.\r\n- Step up. Step up.\r\n\r\n587\r\n00:59:11,760 --> 00:59:14,058\r\nWhere you going? Where you going?\r\n\r\n588\r\n00:59:17,932 --> 00:59:19,263\r\nAin't this a party now?\r\n\r\n589\r\n00:59:19,567 --> 00:59:20,795\r\n- Is it or what?\r\n- Let him go.\r\n\r\n590\r\n00:59:21,002 --> 00:59:22,629\r\n- Shoot him.\r\n- See who you hit.\r\n\r\n591\r\n00:59:22,837 --> 00:59:24,771\r\n- Shoot the son of a bitch.\r\n- Shoot me!\r\n\r\n592\r\n00:59:24,939 --> 00:59:28,306\r\n- Shoot him!\r\n- Hit him, Percy! Goddamn it! Hit him.\r\n\r\n593\r\n00:59:28,510 --> 00:59:29,977\r\nHit me, you limp noodle.\r\n\r\n594\r\n00:59:30,178 --> 00:59:32,476\r\nHit him, Percy!\r\nGoddamn it, hit him!\r\n\r\n595\r\n00:59:32,680 --> 00:59:35,649\r\n- Come on, Percy. Hit me.\r\n- Wharton, I'm warning you.\r\n\r\n596\r\n00:59:35,850 --> 00:59:38,683\r\n- You warning me? Warn me now.\r\n- I'm warning you!\r\n\r\n597\r\n00:59:38,887 --> 00:59:40,912\r\n- You're warning me?!\r\n- Shoot him!\r\n\r\n598\r\n00:59:41,122 --> 00:59:42,487\r\nWell, come on...\r\n\r\n599\r\n00:59:49,063 --> 00:59:50,962\r\nYou're a big fucker.\r\n\r\n600\r\n00:59:51,331 --> 00:59:52,764\r\nWhere'd you come from?\r\n\r\n601\r\n01:00:03,377 --> 01:00:05,868\r\nCome on, Dean.\r\nCome on, boy, get up.\r\n\r\n602\r\n01:00:06,079 --> 01:00:07,637\r\nAll right. Now, just breathe.\r\n\r\n603\r\n01:00:08,215 --> 01:00:10,308\r\nThat's it. Just breathe.\r\nJust breathe.\r\n\r\n604\r\n01:00:12,186 --> 01:00:13,915\r\nBreathe. Breathe, boy.\r\n\r\n605\r\n01:00:14,154 --> 01:00:17,123\r\n- Didn't see it coming.\r\n- Come on, boy, breathe.\r\n\r\n606\r\n01:00:17,324 --> 01:00:19,349\r\nCome on. Just breathe.\r\n\r\n607\r\n01:00:22,196 --> 01:00:24,323\r\nWe thought he was doped.\r\n\r\n608\r\n01:00:25,599 --> 01:00:28,864\r\nDidn't we? Didn't we, all of us,\r\nthink he was doped?\r\n\r\n609\r\n01:00:29,069 --> 01:00:30,798\r\nYou didn't ask?\r\n\r\n610\r\n01:00:32,105 --> 01:00:33,970\r\nWell, I guess that's not a mistake...\r\n\r\n611\r\n01:00:34,341 --> 01:00:37,571\r\n...you'll be needing to make again\r\nanytime soon, is it?\r\n\r\n612\r\n01:00:51,624 --> 01:00:55,253\r\nYou go get Dean and Harry looked at.\r\nMake sure they're all right.\r\n\r\n613\r\n01:00:55,695 --> 01:00:59,222\r\nPercy, you make the report\r\nto the warden for me.\r\n\r\n614\r\n01:00:59,432 --> 01:01:01,992\r\nSay the situation's under control.\r\nIt's not a story.\r\n\r\n615\r\n01:01:02,201 --> 01:01:04,863\r\nHe won't appreciate you\r\ndrawing out the suspense.\r\n\r\n616\r\n01:01:05,071 --> 01:01:07,301\r\nWhat about you?\r\nYou're about to collapse.\r\n\r\n617\r\n01:01:07,540 --> 01:01:10,873\r\nI've got the Mile\r\ntill you all come back.\r\n\r\n618\r\n01:01:11,644 --> 01:01:13,612\r\nGo on, now. Go.\r\n\r\n619\r\n01:01:21,286 --> 01:01:24,414\r\nCome on, boy.\r\nLet's get you looked at.\r\n\r\n620\r\n01:01:50,015 --> 01:01:53,451\r\nBoss, I needs to see you down here.\r\n\r\n621\r\n01:01:56,988 --> 01:02:00,219\r\nThis is not a good time, John Coffey...\r\n\r\n622\r\n01:02:00,425 --> 01:02:02,393\r\n...not a good time at all.\r\n\r\n623\r\n01:02:02,594 --> 01:02:06,723\r\nBut I needs to see you, boss.\r\nI needs to talk to you.\r\n\r\n624\r\n01:02:28,786 --> 01:02:30,083\r\nCloser.\r\n\r\n625\r\n01:02:30,621 --> 01:02:32,680\r\nBoss, you know you ain't\r\nsupposed to do that.\r\n\r\n626\r\n01:02:34,325 --> 01:02:36,293\r\nMind your business, Del.\r\n\r\n627\r\n01:02:45,936 --> 01:02:47,961\r\nWhat do you want, John Coffey?\r\n\r\n628\r\n01:02:49,038 --> 01:02:50,130\r\nJust to help it.\r\n\r\n629\r\n01:02:53,810 --> 01:02:55,243\r\nDon't be afraid.\r\n\r\n630\r\n01:02:55,812 --> 01:02:56,836\r\nHelp!\r\n\r\n631\r\n01:02:57,647 --> 01:03:00,445\r\nHelp! John Coffey's\r\nkilling Boss Edgecomb!\r\n\r\n632\r\n01:03:00,616 --> 01:03:02,140\r\nHelp!\r\n\r\n633\r\n01:03:02,352 --> 01:03:05,583\r\n- What are you doing?\r\n- Help!\r\n\r\n634\r\n01:03:08,157 --> 01:03:10,022\r\nBoss Howell! Help!\r\n\r\n635\r\n01:03:10,727 --> 01:03:12,456\r\nBoss Stanton! Somebody, come!\r\n\r\n636\r\n01:03:12,795 --> 01:03:14,763\r\nHelp!\r\n\r\n637\r\n01:03:31,180 --> 01:03:33,410\r\nHelp! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!\r\n\r\n638\r\n01:03:33,616 --> 01:03:36,584\r\nSomebody, come!\r\nJohn Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!\r\n\r\n639\r\n01:03:36,785 --> 01:03:39,413\r\nDel, for chrissakes, shut up!\r\n\r\n640\r\n01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:28,230\r\nWhat did you just do to me?\r\n\r\n641\r\n01:04:30,204 --> 01:04:31,899\r\nI helped it.\r\n\r\n642\r\n01:04:32,973 --> 01:04:34,600\r\nDidn't I help it?\r\n\r\n643\r\n01:04:35,709 --> 01:04:37,939\r\nI just took it back, is all.\r\n\r\n644\r\n01:04:38,746 --> 01:04:41,214\r\nAwful tired now, boss.\r\n\r\n645\r\n01:04:41,749 --> 01:04:43,444\r\nDog-tired.\r\n\r\n646\r\n01:05:07,574 --> 01:05:10,600\r\nBoss, what that man do to you?\r\n\r\n647\r\n01:06:13,071 --> 01:06:15,835\r\nHey, honey. How you feeling?\r\n\r\n648\r\n01:06:17,643 --> 01:06:20,407\r\nOh, not too bad.\r\n\r\n649\r\n01:06:21,647 --> 01:06:23,410\r\nWhat did the doctor say?\r\n\r\n650\r\n01:06:25,651 --> 01:06:27,380\r\nOh, you know doctors.\r\n\r\n651\r\n01:06:27,819 --> 01:06:29,719\r\nGobbledygook, mostly.\r\n\r\n652\r\n01:06:30,822 --> 01:06:32,187\r\nGobbledygook.\r\n\r\n653\r\n01:06:47,438 --> 01:06:49,030\r\nHaving stew tonight.\r\n\r\n654\r\n01:06:59,350 --> 01:07:01,045\r\nWhat are you doing?\r\n\r\n655\r\n01:07:07,758 --> 01:07:09,623\r\nWhat does it feel like?\r\n\r\n656\r\n01:07:10,494 --> 01:07:12,928\r\nWell, I know what it feels like.\r\n\r\n657\r\n01:07:16,567 --> 01:07:18,466\r\nIt feels great.\r\n\r\n658\r\n01:07:52,897 --> 01:07:54,797\r\n- Paul.\r\n- Yeah?\r\n\r\n659\r\n01:07:55,232 --> 01:07:57,962\r\nNot that I'm complaining...\r\n\r\n660\r\n01:07:59,103 --> 01:08:02,833\r\n...but we haven't gone four times\r\nin one night since we were 19.\r\n\r\n661\r\n01:08:03,073 --> 01:08:05,439\r\nYeah, we did, at your mom's.\r\n\r\n662\r\n01:08:06,943 --> 01:08:08,934\r\nWanna tell me what's going on?\r\n\r\n663\r\n01:08:12,749 --> 01:08:14,114\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n664\r\n01:08:15,418 --> 01:08:17,409\r\n...see, the thing is...\r\n\r\n665\r\n01:08:18,621 --> 01:08:22,182\r\n...I never actually made it in\r\nto Dr. Bishop's yesterday.\r\n\r\n666\r\n01:08:25,362 --> 01:08:28,160\r\nBrutal, Paul. Listen.\r\n\r\n667\r\n01:08:28,365 --> 01:08:32,802\r\nI'm thinking of taking the morning\r\noff sick. You cover the fort for me?\r\n\r\n668\r\n01:08:33,870 --> 01:08:36,134\r\nThat's swell. Thanks.\r\n\r\n669\r\n01:08:36,339 --> 01:08:38,967\r\nYeah, no, I'm sure I'll feel better.\r\n\r\n670\r\n01:08:39,209 --> 01:08:41,837\r\nOkay. Okay.\r\n\r\n671\r\n01:08:47,217 --> 01:08:49,184\r\nYou're sure you ought to do this?\r\n\r\n672\r\n01:08:50,786 --> 01:08:53,016\r\nI'm not sure what I'm sure of.\r\n\r\n673\r\n01:09:09,838 --> 01:09:12,830\r\nBurt, you got some company.\r\n\r\n674\r\n01:09:13,509 --> 01:09:15,101\r\nCan I offer you a cold drink?\r\n\r\n675\r\n01:09:15,344 --> 01:09:18,438\r\nOh, yes, ma'am. A cold drink\r\nwould be fine. Thank you.\r\n\r\n676\r\n01:09:18,781 --> 01:09:21,875\r\nMr. Hammersmith, your office said\r\nI might find you at home.\r\n\r\n677\r\n01:09:22,084 --> 01:09:23,745\r\nHope I'm not troubling you.\r\n\r\n678\r\n01:09:24,420 --> 01:09:26,513\r\nWell, that depends, Mr?\r\n\r\n679\r\n01:09:26,722 --> 01:09:30,749\r\nPaul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor\r\nup on Cold Mountain.\r\n\r\n680\r\n01:09:31,960 --> 01:09:33,324\r\nThe Green Mile.\r\n\r\n681\r\n01:09:33,528 --> 01:09:36,656\r\nYeah, I've heard of it.\r\nLost a few clients your way.\r\n\r\n682\r\n01:09:37,432 --> 01:09:40,026\r\nI'd like to ask you about one of them.\r\n\r\n683\r\n01:09:41,302 --> 01:09:43,293\r\n- Have a seat.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n684\r\n01:09:48,042 --> 01:09:49,805\r\nWhich client?\r\n\r\n685\r\n01:09:51,279 --> 01:09:54,077\r\nNow you got my curiosity aroused.\r\n\r\n686\r\n01:09:54,282 --> 01:09:55,613\r\nJohn Coffey.\r\n\r\n687\r\n01:09:56,818 --> 01:09:58,217\r\nCoffey.\r\n\r\n688\r\n01:09:58,386 --> 01:09:59,614\r\nHe causing you problems?\r\n\r\n689\r\n01:10:00,088 --> 01:10:03,649\r\nNo. Can't say he is. He doesn't like\r\nthe dark and cries on occasion...\r\n\r\n690\r\n01:10:03,858 --> 01:10:05,723\r\n...but other than that...\r\n\r\n691\r\n01:10:05,893 --> 01:10:09,192\r\nHe cries, does he?\r\nWell, got a lot to cry about, I'd say.\r\n\r\n692\r\n01:10:09,397 --> 01:10:10,955\r\nYou know what he did.\r\n\r\n693\r\n01:10:11,632 --> 01:10:13,657\r\nI read the court transcript.\r\n\r\n694\r\n01:10:14,569 --> 01:10:17,332\r\n- Thank you, missus.\r\n- My pleasure.\r\n\r\n695\r\n01:10:18,205 --> 01:10:21,504\r\nKids! Lunch is about ready.\r\nY'all come on up.\r\n\r\n696\r\n01:10:21,741 --> 01:10:23,038\r\n- Coming, Mama!\r\n- Coming, Mama!\r\n\r\n697\r\n01:10:23,243 --> 01:10:26,371\r\nWhat exactly are you\r\ntrying to find out?\r\n\r\n698\r\n01:10:26,980 --> 01:10:29,312\r\nI've wondered if he did anything\r\nlike that before.\r\n\r\n699\r\n01:10:30,784 --> 01:10:32,752\r\nWhy? Has he said anything?\r\n\r\n700\r\n01:10:32,953 --> 01:10:36,116\r\nNo, but a man who does\r\na thing like that...\r\n\r\n701\r\n01:10:36,323 --> 01:10:40,225\r\n...has often developed a taste for it\r\nover time. It occurred to me...\r\n\r\n702\r\n01:10:40,427 --> 01:10:44,329\r\n...that it might be easy enough\r\nto follow his back trail. Find out.\r\n\r\n703\r\n01:10:45,098 --> 01:10:48,898\r\nA man his size, and colored to boot,\r\ncan't be that hard to trace.\r\n\r\n704\r\n01:10:49,102 --> 01:10:52,094\r\nYou'd think so, but you'd be wrong.\r\n\r\n705\r\n01:10:52,305 --> 01:10:54,432\r\nBelieve me, we tried.\r\n\r\n706\r\n01:10:55,275 --> 01:10:57,470\r\nLike he'd dropped out of the sky.\r\n\r\n707\r\n01:10:58,278 --> 01:10:59,711\r\nHow can that be?\r\n\r\n708\r\n01:10:59,946 --> 01:11:04,143\r\nWe're in a depression.\r\nA third of the country's out of work.\r\n\r\n709\r\n01:11:04,350 --> 01:11:08,377\r\nPeople are drifting by the thousands,\r\nlooking for jobs, for greener grass.\r\n\r\n710\r\n01:11:08,621 --> 01:11:11,749\r\nEven a giant like Coffey\r\nwouldn't get noticed everywhere.\r\n\r\n711\r\n01:11:12,525 --> 01:11:14,857\r\nNot until he kills\r\na couple of little girls.\r\n\r\n712\r\n01:11:15,694 --> 01:11:17,286\r\nHe is...\r\n\r\n713\r\n01:11:17,630 --> 01:11:19,689\r\n...strange, I admit.\r\n\r\n714\r\n01:11:20,065 --> 01:11:24,365\r\nBut there doesn't seem to be\r\nany real violence in him.\r\n\r\n715\r\n01:11:24,803 --> 01:11:27,237\r\nI know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.\r\n\r\n716\r\n01:11:27,473 --> 01:11:30,306\r\nI deal with them day in and day out.\r\n\r\n717\r\n01:11:31,110 --> 01:11:33,772\r\nYou didn't come to ask me\r\nwhether he killed before.\r\n\r\n718\r\n01:11:33,979 --> 01:11:36,914\r\nYou came to see if I think\r\nhe did it at all.\r\n\r\n719\r\n01:11:38,317 --> 01:11:40,012\r\nDo you?\r\n\r\n720\r\n01:11:41,220 --> 01:11:43,381\r\nOne seldom sees a less ambiguous case.\r\n\r\n721\r\n01:11:43,589 --> 01:11:45,648\r\nHe was found with the victims\r\nin his arms.\r\n\r\n722\r\n01:11:45,858 --> 01:11:47,654\r\nAnd yet you defended him.\r\n\r\n723\r\n01:11:48,660 --> 01:11:51,254\r\nEveryone is entitled to a defense.\r\n\r\n724\r\n01:11:51,663 --> 01:11:53,290\r\nKids! Lunch!\r\n\r\n725\r\n01:11:53,498 --> 01:11:54,795\r\nY'all listen to your mama!\r\n\r\n726\r\n01:11:59,437 --> 01:12:00,995\r\nI'll tell you something.\r\n\r\n727\r\n01:12:02,073 --> 01:12:05,668\r\nAnd you listen close too, because it\r\nmight be something you need to know.\r\n\r\n728\r\n01:12:05,877 --> 01:12:07,242\r\nI'm listening.\r\n\r\n729\r\n01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,614\r\nWe had us a dog.\r\n\r\n730\r\n01:12:10,782 --> 01:12:12,807\r\nJust a sweet mongrel.\r\n\r\n731\r\n01:12:13,017 --> 01:12:14,507\r\nYou know the kind.\r\n\r\n732\r\n01:12:15,887 --> 01:12:19,323\r\nWell, in many ways,\r\na good mongrel dog is like a Negro.\r\n\r\n733\r\n01:12:20,191 --> 01:12:21,954\r\nYou get to know it.\r\n\r\n734\r\n01:12:22,160 --> 01:12:26,529\r\nOften, you get to love it.\r\nIt is of no particular use...\r\n\r\n735\r\n01:12:26,731 --> 01:12:30,258\r\n...but you keep it around\r\nbecause you think it loves you.\r\n\r\n736\r\n01:12:31,768 --> 01:12:35,898\r\nIf you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you\r\nnever have to find out any different.\r\n\r\n737\r\n01:12:36,974 --> 01:12:39,169\r\nMy wife and I were not so lucky.\r\n\r\n738\r\n01:12:41,144 --> 01:12:42,668\r\nCaleb, come here for a second.\r\n\r\n739\r\n01:12:44,081 --> 01:12:45,275\r\nCome here.\r\n\r\n740\r\n01:12:46,717 --> 01:12:47,979\r\nPlease, son.\r\n\r\n741\r\n01:12:49,586 --> 01:12:52,054\r\nHe still has the one good eye.\r\n\r\n742\r\n01:12:53,423 --> 01:12:55,687\r\nI suppose he's lucky...\r\n\r\n743\r\n01:12:55,892 --> 01:12:58,258\r\n...not to be completely blind.\r\n\r\n744\r\n01:13:00,964 --> 01:13:04,730\r\nWe get down on our knees and thank God\r\nfor that much at least.\r\n\r\n745\r\n01:13:05,402 --> 01:13:06,801\r\nRight, Caleb?\r\n\r\n746\r\n01:13:09,273 --> 01:13:10,570\r\nOkay, go on in now.\r\n\r\n747\r\n01:13:14,011 --> 01:13:16,945\r\nThat dog attacked my boy\r\nfor no reason.\r\n\r\n748\r\n01:13:17,546 --> 01:13:19,741\r\nJust got it in his mind one day.\r\n\r\n749\r\n01:13:20,516 --> 01:13:21,983\r\nThe same with John Coffey.\r\n\r\n750\r\n01:13:22,184 --> 01:13:26,416\r\nHe was sorry afterwards.\r\nOf that I have no doubt.\r\n\r\n751\r\n01:13:27,089 --> 01:13:28,954\r\nBut those little girls...\r\n\r\n752\r\n01:13:29,158 --> 01:13:31,592\r\n...stayed raped and murdered.\r\n\r\n753\r\n01:13:32,261 --> 01:13:34,252\r\nMaybe he'd never done it before.\r\n\r\n754\r\n01:13:36,032 --> 01:13:38,193\r\nMy dog never bit before.\r\n\r\n755\r\n01:13:39,935 --> 01:13:42,665\r\nBut I didn't concern myself with that.\r\n\r\n756\r\n01:13:43,673 --> 01:13:47,632\r\nI went out with my rifle, grabbed\r\nhis collar and blew his brains out.\r\n\r\n757\r\n01:13:49,011 --> 01:13:50,171\r\nIs Coffey guilty?\r\n\r\n758\r\n01:13:53,115 --> 01:13:54,844\r\nYes, he is.\r\n\r\n759\r\n01:13:55,451 --> 01:13:57,112\r\nDon't you doubt it.\r\n