 --> 02:41:47,748\r\nI'm tired of all the pain\r\nI feel and hear in the world...\r\n\r\n1627\r\n02:41:47,959 --> 02:41:49,620\r\n...every day.\r\n\r\n1628\r\n02:41:49,995 --> 02:41:51,963\r\nThere's too much of it.\r\n\r\n1629\r\n02:41:52,297 --> 02:41:56,131\r\nIt's like pieces of glass\r\nin my head...\r\n\r\n1630\r\n02:41:56,334 --> 02:41:58,632\r\n...all the time.\r\n\r\n1631\r\n02:42:00,138 --> 02:42:02,197\r\nCan you understand?\r\n\r\n1632\r\n02:42:05,143 --> 02:42:08,112\r\nYes, John, I think I can.\r\n\r\n1633\r\n02:42:10,481 --> 02:42:13,882\r\nWell, there must be something\r\nwe can do for you, John.\r\n\r\n1634\r\n02:42:16,053 --> 02:42:18,078\r\nThere must be something that you want.\r\n\r\n1635\r\n02:42:27,498 --> 02:42:31,992\r\nI ain't never seen me a flicker show.\r\n\r\n1636\r\n02:42:32,503 --> 02:42:34,630\r\n<i>Neaven</i>\r\n\r\n1637\r\n02:42:34,839 --> 02:42:37,000\r\n<i>I'm in heaven</i>\r\n\r\n1638\r\n02:42:37,908 --> 02:42:43,505\r\n<i>And my heart beats so\r\nThat I can hardly speak</i>\r\n\r\n1639\r\n02:42:44,582 --> 02:42:50,543\r\n<i>And I seem to find\r\nThe happiness I seek</i>\r\n\r\n1640\r\n02:42:51,021 --> 02:42:56,890\r\n<i>When we're out together\r\nDancing cheek to cheek</i>\r\n\r\n1641\r\n02:43:57,920 --> 02:44:00,354\r\nWhy, they's angels.\r\n\r\n1642\r\n02:44:01,256 --> 02:44:03,918\r\nAngels, just like up in heaven.\r\n\r\n1643\r\n02:45:04,585 --> 02:45:06,576\r\nI'll be all right, fellas.\r\n\r\n1644\r\n02:45:07,988 --> 02:45:10,252\r\nThis here's the hard part.\r\n\r\n1645\r\n02:45:11,558 --> 02:45:13,082\r\nI'll be all right in a while.\r\n\r\n1646\r\n02:45:14,160 --> 02:45:18,756\r\nJohn, I should have this just for now.\r\n\r\n1647\r\n02:45:22,769 --> 02:45:25,203\r\nI'll give it back after.\r\n\r\n1648\r\n02:45:28,341 --> 02:45:32,869\r\nYou know, I fell asleep this afternoon\r\nand had me a dream.\r\n\r\n1649\r\n02:45:34,080 --> 02:45:36,173\r\nI dreamed about Del's mouse.\r\n\r\n1650\r\n02:45:37,350 --> 02:45:38,578\r\nDid you, John?\r\n\r\n1651\r\n02:45:39,352 --> 02:45:43,755\r\nI dreamed Mr. Jingles got down to\r\nthat place Boss Howell talked about.\r\n\r\n1652\r\n02:45:43,957 --> 02:45:46,255\r\nThat Mouseville place.\r\n\r\n1653\r\n02:45:46,526 --> 02:45:48,858\r\nI dreamed there's kids.\r\n\r\n1654\r\n02:45:49,429 --> 02:45:52,864\r\nAnd how they laughed\r\nat his tricks. My!\r\n\r\n1655\r\n02:45:55,367 --> 02:45:59,167\r\nI dreamed that those two little\r\nblond-headed girls was there.\r\n\r\n1656\r\n02:45:59,371 --> 02:46:01,236\r\nThey's laughing too.\r\n\r\n1657\r\n02:46:01,440 --> 02:46:04,375\r\nI put my arms around them\r\nand set them on my knees.\r\n\r\n1658\r\n02:46:04,576 --> 02:46:08,637\r\nAnd they was no blood coming out\r\nof they hair, and they's just fine.\r\n\r\n1659\r\n02:46:08,881 --> 02:46:12,214\r\nWe all watched Mr. Jingles\r\nroll that spool.\r\n\r\n1660\r\n02:46:13,719 --> 02:46:17,155\r\nHow we did laugh.\r\nFit to bust, we was!\r\n\r\n1661\r\n02:46:32,938 --> 02:46:34,735\r\nJohn.\r\n\r\n1662\r\n02:46:35,407 --> 02:46:40,400\r\nThey's lots of folks here\r\nthat hate me. Lots!\r\n\r\n1663\r\n02:46:41,412 --> 02:46:43,471\r\nI can feel it.\r\n\r\n1664\r\n02:46:43,681 --> 02:46:45,410\r\nIt's like bees stinging me.\r\n\r\n1665\r\n02:46:45,750 --> 02:46:48,116\r\nWell, feel how we feel, then.\r\n\r\n1666\r\n02:46:49,420 --> 02:46:50,648\r\nWe don't hate you.\r\n\r\n1667\r\n02:46:52,023 --> 02:46:53,581\r\nCan you feel that?\r\n\r\n1668\r\n02:46:55,827 --> 02:46:57,988\r\nKill him twice, you boys!\r\n\r\n1669\r\n02:46:58,763 --> 02:47:02,756\r\nYou go on and kill that raping\r\nbaby killer twice!\r\n\r\n1670\r\n02:47:02,967 --> 02:47:04,798\r\nThat'd be fine!\r\n\r\n1671\r\n02:47:21,486 --> 02:47:23,953\r\nWipe your face before\r\nyou stand up, Dean.\r\n\r\n1672\r\n02:47:24,154 --> 02:47:25,451\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n1673\r\n02:47:37,734 --> 02:47:38,792\r\nRoll on one.\r\n\r\n1674\r\n02:47:46,810 --> 02:47:50,337\r\nDoes it hurt yet? I hope it does.\r\n\r\n1675\r\n02:47:51,148 --> 02:47:53,412\r\nI hope it hurts like hell.\r\n\r\n1676\r\n02:47:55,352 --> 02:47:59,413\r\nJohn Coffey, you've been condemned to die\r\nin the electric chair by a jury of your peers.\r\n\r\n1677\r\n02:47:59,656 --> 02:48:03,217\r\nSentence imposed by a judge\r\nin good standing in this state.\r\n\r\n1678\r\n02:48:03,527 --> 02:48:06,758\r\nDo you have anything to say\r\nbefore sentence is carried out?\r\n\r\n1679\r\n02:48:08,497 --> 02:48:11,022\r\nI'm sorry for what I am.\r\n\r\n1680\r\n02:48:23,045 --> 02:48:24,774\r\nPlease, boss...\r\n\r\n1681\r\n02:48:26,182 --> 02:48:28,878\r\n...don't put that thing over my face.\r\n\r\n1682\r\n02:48:30,086 --> 02:48:32,418\r\nDon't put me in the dark.\r\n\r\n1683\r\n02:48:33,189 --> 02:48:35,521\r\nI's afraid of the dark.\r\n\r\n1684\r\n02:48:45,201 --> 02:48:46,862\r\nAll right, John.\r\n\r\n1685\r\n02:49:07,055 --> 02:49:10,081\r\n<i>Neaven, I'm in heaven</i>\r\n\r\n1686\r\n02:49:10,291 --> 02:49:13,124\r\n<i>Neaven, heaven</i>\r\n\r\n1687\r\n02:49:13,328 --> 02:49:15,159\r\n<i>I'm in heaven</i>\r\n\r\n1688\r\n02:49:15,730 --> 02:49:18,324\r\n<i>Neaven, heaven</i>\r\n\r\n1689\r\n02:49:18,566 --> 02:49:20,261\r\n<i>I'm in heaven</i>\r\n\r\n1690\r\n02:49:41,188 --> 02:49:42,780\r\nJohn Coffey...\r\n\r\n1691\r\n02:49:43,824 --> 02:49:46,952\r\n...electricity shall pass through\r\nyour body until you are dead...\r\n\r\n1692\r\n02:49:47,161 --> 02:49:49,322\r\n...in accordance with state law.\r\n\r\n1693\r\n02:49:51,698 --> 02:49:55,429\r\nMay God have mercy on your soul.\r\n\r\n1694\r\n02:50:29,769 --> 02:50:30,963\r\nPaul.\r\n\r\n1695\r\n02:50:34,140 --> 02:50:36,074\r\nYou have to say it.\r\n\r\n1696\r\n02:50:37,743 --> 02:50:40,041\r\nYou have to give the order.\r\n\r\n1697\r\n02:50:58,064 --> 02:51:00,362\r\n<i>Ne killed them with they love.</i>\r\n\r\n1698\r\n02:51:00,566 --> 02:51:05,401\r\n<i>That's how it is every day\r\nall over the world.</i>\r\n\r\n1699\r\n02:51:19,184 --> 02:51:20,651\r\nRoll on two.\r\n\r\n1700\r\n02:53:05,288 --> 02:53:08,655\r\n<i>It was the last execution\r\nI ever took part in.</i>\r\n\r\n1701\r\n02:53:08,958 --> 02:53:12,689\r\nI just couldn't do it anymore\r\nafter that. Brutal either.\r\n\r\n1702\r\n02:53:13,863 --> 02:53:18,562\r\nWe both transferred out,\r\ntook jobs with Boys' Correctional.\r\n\r\n1703\r\n02:53:18,801 --> 02:53:20,563\r\nIt was all right.\r\n\r\n1704\r\n02:53:21,203 --> 02:53:24,138\r\n\"Catch them young\" became my motto.\r\n\r\n1705\r\n02:53:27,376 --> 02:53:28,502\r\nYou don't believe me.\r\n\r\n1706\r\n02:53:29,378 --> 02:53:31,903\r\nI don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.\r\n\r\n1707\r\n02:53:32,714 --> 02:53:34,875\r\n- It's just that...\r\n- It's quite a story.\r\n\r\n1708\r\n02:53:35,083 --> 02:53:37,313\r\nIt's quite a story.\r\n\r\n1709\r\n02:53:37,719 --> 02:53:40,085\r\nOne thing I don't understand.\r\n\r\n1710\r\n02:53:40,322 --> 02:53:42,085\r\nYou said you and Jan...\r\n\r\n1711\r\n02:53:42,324 --> 02:53:45,885\r\n...had a grown son in 1935.\r\n\r\n1712\r\n02:53:46,161 --> 02:53:47,651\r\nIs that right?\r\n\r\n1713\r\n02:53:48,029 --> 02:53:49,997\r\nThe math doesn't work, does it?\r\n\r\n1714\r\n02:53:55,504 --> 02:53:58,268\r\nDo you feel up to taking a walk?\r\n\r\n1715\r\n02:54:18,993 --> 02:54:20,358\r\nWatch your step.\r\n\r\n1716\r\n02:54:20,861 --> 02:54:23,193\r\nNow let your eyes adjust.\r\n\r\n1717\r\n02:54:34,942 --> 02:54:36,068\r\nThere.\r\n\r\n1718\r\n02:54:38,712 --> 02:54:41,613\r\nHey. Wake up, old fella.\r\n\r\n1719\r\n02:54:41,882 --> 02:54:43,144\r\nWake up.\r\n\r\n1720\r\n02:54:46,720 --> 02:54:50,587\r\nPaul, it isn't. It can't be.\r\n\r\n1721\r\n02:54:54,794 --> 02:54:56,125\r\nCome over here, boy.\r\n\r\n1722\r\n02:54:56,629 --> 02:54:58,995\r\nCome on over here and see this lady.\r\n\r\n1723\r\n02:55:01,901 --> 02:55:04,927\r\nThat can't be Mr. Jingles.\r\n\r\n1724\r\n02:55:27,594 --> 02:55:30,188\r\nGo on, you can do it.\r\n\r\n1725\r\n02:55:37,269 --> 02:55:41,763\r\nThis isn't exactly the Mouseville\r\nwe had in mind, is it?\r\n\r\n1726\r\n02:55:42,541 --> 02:55:46,500\r\nBut we make do. Don't we, old fella?\r\n\r\n1727\r\n02:55:52,951 --> 02:55:56,614\r\nI think Mr. Jingles\r\nhappened by accident.\r\n\r\n1728\r\n02:55:57,055 --> 02:56:01,924\r\nI think when we electrocuted Del,\r\nand it all went so badly...\r\n\r\n1729\r\n02:56:02,127 --> 02:56:04,527\r\n...well, John could feel that,\r\nyou know.\r\n\r\n1730\r\n02:56:04,730 --> 02:56:08,131\r\nAnd I think a part of...\r\n\r\n1731\r\n02:56:08,367 --> 02:56:11,131\r\n...whatever magic was inside of him...\r\n\r\n1732\r\n02:56:11,303 --> 02:56:14,636\r\n...just leapt into my tiny friend here.\r\n\r\n1733\r\n02:56:15,807 --> 02:56:17,798\r\nAs for me...\r\n\r\n1734\r\n02:56:18,977 --> 02:56:21,536\r\n...John had to give me\r\na part of himself...\r\n\r\n1735\r\n02:56:21,812 --> 02:56:23,973\r\n...a gift, the way he saw it...\r\n\r\n1736\r\n02:56:24,315 --> 02:56:27,751\r\n...so that I could see for myself\r\nwhat Wild Bill had done.\r\n\r\n1737\r\n02:56:30,154 --> 02:56:32,384\r\nWhen John did that...\r\n\r\n1738\r\n02:56:33,824 --> 02:56:36,156\r\n...when he took my hand...\r\n\r\n1739\r\n02:56:37,161 --> 02:56:41,063\r\n...a part of the power\r\nthat worked through him...\r\n\r\n1740\r\n02:56:41,999 --> 02:56:43,864\r\n...spilled into me.\r\n\r\n1741\r\n02:56:44,235 --> 02:56:46,066\r\nHe what?\r\n\r\n1742\r\n02:56:46,504 --> 02:56:50,031\r\nHe infected you with life?\r\n\r\n1743\r\n02:56:51,609 --> 02:56:53,941\r\nIt's as good a word as any.\r\n\r\n1744\r\n02:56:55,446 --> 02:56:58,347\r\nHe infected us both,\r\ndidn't he, Mr. Jingles?\r\n\r\n1745\r\n02:56:58,549 --> 02:57:00,016\r\nWith life.\r\n\r\n1746\r\n02:57:04,088 --> 02:57:07,181\r\nI'm 108 years old, Elaine.\r\n\r\n1747\r\n02:57:07,424 --> 02:57:11,793\r\nI was 44 the year that John Coffey\r\nwalked the Green Mile.\r\n\r\n1748\r\n02:57:14,698 --> 02:57:18,464\r\nYou mustn't blame John.\r\nHe couldn't help what happened.\r\n\r\n1749\r\n02:57:18,702 --> 02:57:23,264\r\nHe was just a force of nature.\r\n\r\n1750\r\n02:57:23,707 --> 02:57:27,905\r\nOh, I've lived to see\r\nsome amazing things, Ellie.\r\n\r\n1751\r\n02:57:28,945 --> 02:57:31,914\r\nAnother century come to pass.\r\n\r\n1752\r\n02:57:32,148 --> 02:57:34,013\r\nBut I've...\r\n\r\n1753\r\n02:57:34,651 --> 02:57:39,111\r\nI've had to see my friends and\r\nloved ones die off through the years.\r\n\r\n1754\r\n02:57:39,489 --> 02:57:41,548\r\nHal and Melinda...\r\n\r\n1755\r\n02:57:41,992 --> 02:57:43,425\r\n...Brutus Howell...\r\n\r\n1756\r\n02:57:43,627 --> 02:57:46,289\r\n...my wife, my boy.\r\n\r\n1757\r\n02:57:49,232 --> 02:57:51,096\r\nAnd you, Elaine.\r\n\r\n1758\r\n02:57:52,101 --> 02:57:53,898\r\nYou'll die too.\r\n\r\n1759\r\n02:57:55,404 --> 02:57:59,807\r\nAnd my curse is knowing\r\nthat I'll be there to see it.\r\n\r\n1760\r\n02:58:01,243 --> 02:58:03,677\r\nIt's my atonement, you see.\r\n\r\n1761\r\n02:58:04,246 --> 02:58:05,975\r\nIt's my punishment...\r\n\r\n1762\r\n02:58:06,181 --> 02:58:08,809\r\n...for letting John Coffey\r\nride the lightning.\r\n\r\n1763\r\n02:58:10,519 --> 02:58:13,283\r\n<i>For killing a miracle of God.</i>\r\n\r\n1764\r\n02:58:14,823 --> 02:58:17,587\r\n<i>Almighty, everlasting God...</i>\r\n\r\n1765\r\n02:58:17,893 --> 02:58:20,293\r\n...the source of all being and life...\r\n\r\n1766\r\n02:58:20,496 --> 02:58:24,830\r\n<i>You'll be gone like all the others.\r\nI'll have to stay.</i>\r\n\r\n1767\r\n02:58:26,835 --> 02:58:31,033\r\n<i>Oh, I'll die eventually.\r\nOf that I'm sure.</i>\r\n\r\n1768\r\n02:58:31,774 --> 02:58:35,766\r\n<i>I have no illusions of immortality.</i>\r\n\r\n1769\r\n02:58:36,144 --> 02:58:38,738\r\n<i>But I will have wished for death...</i>\r\n\r\n1770\r\n02:58:38,913 --> 02:58:41,541\r\n<i>... long before death finds me.</i>\r\n\r\n1771\r\n02:58:42,650 --> 02:58:46,484\r\n<i>In truth, I wish for it already.</i>\r\n\r\n1772\r\n02:58:58,566 --> 02:59:00,557\r\nMr. Jingles?\r\n\r\n1773\r\n02:59:09,544 --> 02:59:11,705\r\nWhere you been?\r\n\r\n1774\r\n02:59:12,046 --> 02:59:15,413\r\nBeen worried about you, boy.\r\nYou hungry?\r\n\r\n1775\r\n02:59:16,250 --> 02:59:18,684\r\nLet's go see if we can't find you\r\nsomething to eat.\r\n\r\n1776\r\n02:59:19,820 --> 02:59:23,551\r\nA few crumbs anyway.\r\nI know you'd like that.\r\n\r\n1777\r\n02:59:24,991 --> 02:59:26,322\r\nLook at you.\r\n\r\n1778\r\n02:59:28,028 --> 02:59:31,930\r\n<i>I lie in bed most nights\r\nthinking about it.</i>\r\n\r\n1779\r\n02:59:32,132 --> 02:59:34,157\r\n<i>And I wait.</i>\r\n\r\n1780\r\n02:59:34,868 --> 02:59:37,803\r\n<i>I think about all the people\r\nI've loved...</i>\r\n\r\n1781\r\n02:59:38,004 --> 02:59:40,165\r\n<i>... now long gone.</i>\r\n\r\n1782\r\n02:59:40,741 --> 02:59:43,335\r\n<i>I think about my beautiful Jan...</i>\r\n\r\n1783\r\n02:59:43,543 --> 02:59:46,569\r\n<i>... how I lost her so many years ago.</i>\r\n\r\n1784\r\n02:59:47,948 --> 02:59:52,578\r\n<i>And I think about all of us walking\r\nour own Green Mile...</i>\r\n\r\n1785\r\n02:59:52,786 --> 02:59:55,448\r\n<i>... each in our own time.</i>\r\n\r\n1786\r\n02:59:56,523 --> 02:59:59,720\r\n<i>But one thought\r\nmore than any other...</i>\r\n\r\n1787\r\n02:59:59,926 --> 03:00:02,554\r\n<i>... keeps me awake most nights:</i>\r\n\r\n1788\r\n03:00:03,729 --> 03:00:07,688\r\n<i>If he could make a mouse\r\nlive so long...</i>\r\n\r\n1789\r\n03:00:08,033 --> 03:00:11,264\r\n<i>... how much longer do I have?</i>\r\n\r\n1790\r\n03:00:14,573 --> 03:00:17,337\r\n<i>We each owe a death.</i>\r\n\r\n1791\r\n03:00:17,543 --> 03:00:20,034\r\n<i>There are no exceptions.</i>\r\n\r\n1792\r\n03:00:20,813 --> 03:00:22,804\r\n<i>But, oh, God...</i>\r\n\r\n1793\r\n03:00:23,716 --> 03:00:25,513\r\n<i>... sometimes...</i>\r\n\r\n1794\r\n03:00:26,118 --> 03:00:29,713\r\n<i>... the Green Mile seems so long.</i>\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":189,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":1,"column":12},"end":{"row":1,"column":12}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":8,"goalScreenRange":null,"preserveFolds":true},"reversed":false,"tailed":false,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":2,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the.green.mile.(1999).eng.1cd.(6179823) (1)/The Green Mile 1999 BRRiP x264 AC3-BadMeetsEvil-eng.srt","modifiedWhenLastPersisted":false,"digestWhenLastPersisted":"b3c757926e3d60071510fd635996341c45b32696","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"text":"1\r\n00:01:57,229 --> 00:01:59,322\r\n<i>Katie!</i>\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:01:59,899 --> 00:02:01,491\r\n<i>Cora!</i>\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,258\r\n<i>You love your sister?</i>\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:02:03,502 --> 00:02:06,027\r\n<i>You make any noise,\r\nyou know what happens.</i>\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:02:52,484 --> 00:02:54,008\r\nGood morning, Estelle.\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:02:54,219 --> 00:02:57,882\r\n- How am I looking, Paul?\r\n- That's better. That's better.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:03:13,770 --> 00:03:15,761\r\nMorning, Mr. Edgecomb.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:03:15,939 --> 00:03:17,236\r\nSome Danish this morning?\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:03:17,441 --> 00:03:20,638\r\nNo, just two pieces of dry toast,\r\nHector. Thanks.\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:03:20,811 --> 00:03:22,210\r\nLeftover's fine.\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:03:22,412 --> 00:03:25,870\r\n- Dry and cold, same as always.\r\n- Cold is better.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:03:27,551 --> 00:03:29,348\r\nEspecially on those long walks.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:03:30,888 --> 00:03:31,980\r\nAm I right?\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:03:33,557 --> 00:03:37,015\r\nDon't let Nurse Godzilla catch you.\r\nShe'll raise holy hell.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:03:37,194 --> 00:03:39,321\r\nWe're not supposed to let you\r\nwander off.\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:03:42,232 --> 00:03:46,532\r\nWhere do you go every day?\r\nWhat do you do up in those hills?\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:03:47,004 --> 00:03:48,631\r\nJust walk.\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:03:49,239 --> 00:03:50,796\r\nI like to walk.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:03:53,309 --> 00:03:55,300\r\nYou try not to fall down, bust a hip.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:03:55,912 --> 00:03:58,608\r\nI don't wanna be in\r\nno damn search party.\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:05:08,149 --> 00:05:12,483\r\n<i>You want this man constantly in your life?\r\nExplain the moral basis of that.</i>\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:13,745\r\n<i>I've made mistakes.</i>\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:05:13,955 --> 00:05:16,185\r\n<i>Tony doesn't admit that\r\nhe's not a good father.</i>\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:05:16,358 --> 00:05:20,225\r\n<i>She can't ask nothing. You can't\r\nask nothing. I have six kids myself.</i>\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:05:22,029 --> 00:05:23,929\r\nWhy do we always watch this stuff?\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:05:24,732 --> 00:05:26,165\r\nIt's interesting.\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:05:27,167 --> 00:05:31,536\r\nInteresting?\r\nBunch of inbred trailer trash?\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:05:31,739 --> 00:05:34,299\r\nAll they ever talk about is fucking.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:05:34,508 --> 00:05:37,841\r\n<i>- and ain't no way in this green earth\r\nI would have a father like that.</i>\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:05:38,012 --> 00:05:42,711\r\n<i>If what you saying is true...\r\nNo, I'm talking now. I'm talking now.</i>\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:05:42,883 --> 00:05:46,011\r\n<i>- What kind of a mother are you?\r\n- One that causes people more...</i>\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:05:46,186 --> 00:05:48,586\r\n<i>- is going to let you try...</i>\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:05:48,756 --> 00:05:53,989\r\n<i>- You're dead! You can't come back!\r\n- It's back. The Popeil Pocket Fisherman.</i>\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:05:54,161 --> 00:05:56,095\r\n<i>Take my husband, take my kids...</i>\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:05:56,263 --> 00:05:58,197\r\nAre you all right?\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:01,924\r\nYou look tired. You're not yourself.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:06:02,136 --> 00:06:04,797\r\nNo, I'm fine. I promise.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:06:05,204 --> 00:06:08,901\r\nYou're wearing yourself out\r\nwith those walks every day, I think.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:06:09,108 --> 00:06:11,042\r\nNot that you asked me.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:06:11,377 --> 00:06:14,210\r\nI just didn't sleep well, is all.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:06:15,214 --> 00:06:18,513\r\nI had a few bad dreams. It happens.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:06:18,718 --> 00:06:20,379\r\nI'll be fine.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:06:28,928 --> 00:06:31,522\r\n<i>If Madge doesn't care,\r\nI certainly don't.</i>\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:06:31,731 --> 00:06:32,857\r\n<i>Neither do I.</i>\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:35,691\r\nNow, this here is worth a look.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:06:37,537 --> 00:06:39,437\r\n<i>I'm in heaven</i>\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:46,374\r\n<i>And my heart beats so\r\nThat I can hardly speak</i>\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:06:47,046 --> 00:06:48,979\r\n<i>And I seem to find</i>\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:06:49,181 --> 00:06:52,878\r\n<i>The happiness I seek</i>\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:06:53,385 --> 00:06:56,354\r\n<i>When we're out together</i>\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:06:56,555 --> 00:06:59,547\r\n<i>Dancing cheek to cheek</i>\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:07:00,592 --> 00:07:02,423\r\n<i>Neaven</i>\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:07:02,994 --> 00:07:05,462\r\n<i>I'm in heaven</i>\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:07:06,364 --> 00:07:08,992\r\n<i>And the cares that hung around me</i>\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:07:09,201 --> 00:07:11,999\r\n<i>Through the week</i>\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:07:12,704 --> 00:07:13,966\r\n<i>Seem to vanish</i>\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:07:14,172 --> 00:07:17,266\r\n<i>Like a gambler's lucky streak</i>\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:07:21,146 --> 00:07:22,579\r\nPaul, what is it?\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,449\r\nMy God.\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:07:31,690 --> 00:07:33,987\r\nI've got to get out of here.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:59,438\r\nI guess sometimes the past\r\njust catches up with you...\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:02,744\r\n...whether you want it to or not.\r\nIt's silly.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:08:03,154 --> 00:08:06,487\r\nWas it the film? It was, wasn't it?\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:08:07,725 --> 00:08:12,162\r\nI haven't spoken of these things\r\nfor a long time, Ellie.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:08:12,363 --> 00:08:13,762\r\nOver 60 years.\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:08:13,964 --> 00:08:16,762\r\nPaul, I'm your friend.\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:08:21,337 --> 00:08:25,068\r\nI ever tell you that I was a prison guard\r\nduring the Depression?\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:08:25,275 --> 00:08:27,140\r\nYou've mentioned it.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:08:28,011 --> 00:08:30,502\r\nDid I mention that I was\r\nin charge of death row?\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:08:30,713 --> 00:08:32,943\r\nThat I supervised all the executions?\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:42,048\r\nUsually, death row is called\r\n\"The Last Mile.\"\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:08:42,392 --> 00:08:44,860\r\nWe called ours \"The Green Mile.\"\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:08:45,562 --> 00:08:48,588\r\nThe floor was the color\r\nof faded limes.\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:08:49,465 --> 00:08:52,093\r\nWe had the electric chair.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:08:52,602 --> 00:08:54,331\r\n\"Old Sparky,\" we called it.\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:08:56,739 --> 00:08:59,572\r\nOh, I've lived a lot of years, Ellie...\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:09:00,376 --> 00:09:04,209\r\n...but 1935, that takes the prize.\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:09:05,547 --> 00:09:07,378\r\nThat year, I had...\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:09:07,549 --> 00:09:10,780\r\n...the worst urinary infection\r\nof my life.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:09:12,487 --> 00:09:13,920\r\nIt was...\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:09:14,957 --> 00:09:17,221\r\nIt was also the year of...\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:09:17,726 --> 00:09:19,921\r\n...John Coffey...\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:09:21,063 --> 00:09:23,497\r\n...and the two dead girls.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:10:18,185 --> 00:10:20,312\r\nAll right, now, hold on!\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:10:25,159 --> 00:10:26,456\r\nUp on the tower!\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:10:26,627 --> 00:10:27,924\r\nNew prisoner's coming in!\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:10:28,095 --> 00:10:31,758\r\nYou men down in the yard,\r\nstep off the fence! Clear that gate!\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:10:38,571 --> 00:10:40,095\r\nPut me through to E Block.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:10:54,087 --> 00:10:55,520\r\nE Block.\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:10:55,956 --> 00:10:57,287\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:10:57,757 --> 00:10:58,985\r\nRight.\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:11:20,045 --> 00:11:22,411\r\nPaul? Prisoner.\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:11:22,614 --> 00:11:24,206\r\nChrist, give me a minute.\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:11:29,788 --> 00:11:31,016\r\nYou all right in there?\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:11:33,692 --> 00:11:37,628\r\nFor a man pissing razorblades, yeah.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:11:52,111 --> 00:11:54,511\r\nYou should've took the day off\r\nto see the doctor.\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:57,443\r\nWith a new arrival?\r\nYou know better.\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,540\r\nBesides...\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:03,543\r\n...it's not as bad as it was.\r\nI think it's clearing up.\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:12:06,190 --> 00:12:08,488\r\n- All right. Let's look alive, Dean.\r\n- Yes, sir.\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,094\r\nDamn.\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:12:18,403 --> 00:12:20,394\r\nThey're riding on the axle.\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:12:30,014 --> 00:12:31,447\r\nWhat'd they do?\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:33,444\r\nThey bust the springs?\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:12:42,193 --> 00:12:43,751\r\nDead man!\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:12:44,529 --> 00:12:46,190\r\nDead man walking!\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:12:47,597 --> 00:12:49,929\r\nWe got a dead man walking here!\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:53,258\r\nJesus, please us,\r\nwhat is he yelling about?\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:12:56,139 --> 00:12:57,766\r\nPaul...\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:12:58,442 --> 00:13:01,377\r\n...you might reconsider getting\r\nin the cell with this guy.\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:13:01,578 --> 00:13:03,011\r\nHe's enormous.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:13:03,213 --> 00:13:05,181\r\nCan't be bigger than you.\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:13:15,659 --> 00:13:16,990\r\nDead man!\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:13:17,661 --> 00:13:19,322\r\nDead man walking!\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:13:19,529 --> 00:13:20,996\r\nDead man!\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:13:21,531 --> 00:13:22,725\r\nDead man walking!\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,893\r\nDead man walking here!\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:13:27,170 --> 00:13:28,467\r\nDead man!\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:13:32,141 --> 00:13:35,008\r\nWe got a dead man walking here!\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:13:35,544 --> 00:13:36,806\r\nDead man walking!\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:13:38,881 --> 00:13:42,373\r\n- We got a dead man walking here!\r\n- Percy.\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:13:43,085 --> 00:13:44,347\r\nThat's enough.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:14:07,543 --> 00:14:09,977\r\nAm I gonna have any trouble\r\nwith you, big boy?\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,142\r\nCan you talk?\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:14:22,056 --> 00:14:25,719\r\nYes, sir, boss. I can talk.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:14:34,302 --> 00:14:36,827\r\nMove your ass. Let's go.\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:14:37,372 --> 00:14:38,737\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:14:44,045 --> 00:14:45,910\r\nPercy...\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:14:46,481 --> 00:14:49,143\r\n...they're moving house\r\ndown in the infirmary.\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:14:49,717 --> 00:14:52,652\r\nWhy don't you go see\r\nif they could use some help.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:14:53,388 --> 00:14:55,049\r\nThey got all the men they need.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:14:55,723 --> 00:14:57,350\r\nWhy don't you just go\r\nand make sure.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:15:00,228 --> 00:15:03,890\r\nI don't care where you go, as long as\r\nit's not here at this very moment.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:15:08,168 --> 00:15:09,465\r\nAll right.\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:15:22,482 --> 00:15:24,712\r\nGod, you bust my finger.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:15:24,918 --> 00:15:27,318\r\nI wiped that grin off your face,\r\ndidn't I?\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:15:27,521 --> 00:15:30,957\r\nGoddamn it, Percy,\r\nget the hell off my block!\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:15:42,803 --> 00:15:43,929\r\nFuck you, Percy.\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:15:44,137 --> 00:15:47,367\r\nWe'll get that looked at, Del.\r\nIn the meantime, you stay quiet.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:15:48,107 --> 00:15:50,473\r\nYeah. Yeah.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:15:54,046 --> 00:15:56,708\r\nI let Harry take those chains off you...\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:15:57,283 --> 00:15:58,545\r\n...you gonna be nice?\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:16:15,701 --> 00:16:17,225\r\nYour name is John Coffey.\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:16:17,637 --> 00:16:19,229\r\nYes, sir, boss.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:16:19,472 --> 00:16:22,930\r\nLike the drink,\r\nonly not spelt the same.\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:16:23,309 --> 00:16:24,742\r\nOh, you can spell, can you?\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:16:25,578 --> 00:16:28,342\r\nJust my name, boss.\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:16:29,081 --> 00:16:31,446\r\nJ-O...\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:16:31,883 --> 00:16:33,817\r\nMy name is Paul Edgecomb.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:16:34,753 --> 00:16:37,517\r\nIf I'm not here, you can\r\nask for Mr. Terwilliger...\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:16:37,722 --> 00:16:40,816\r\n...Mr. Howell or Mr. Stanton.\r\nThese gentlemen right there.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:16:43,328 --> 00:16:44,488\r\nQuestions?\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:47,630\r\nDo you leave the light on\r\nafter bedtime?\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:16:50,335 --> 00:16:53,827\r\nBecause I get a little scared\r\nin the dark sometime...\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:16:54,506 --> 00:16:57,100\r\n...if it's a strange place.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:17:01,946 --> 00:17:05,973\r\nIt stays pretty bright around here\r\nall night long.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:17:06,184 --> 00:17:08,778\r\nWe always keep a few lights burning\r\nout in the corridor.\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:17:09,888 --> 00:17:11,879\r\nThe corridor?\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:17:13,458 --> 00:17:14,891\r\nRight out there.\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:17:43,053 --> 00:17:44,611\r\nYou can sit.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:18:06,909 --> 00:18:09,275\r\nI couldn't help it, boss.\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:18:09,579 --> 00:18:12,946\r\nI tried to take it back,\r\nbut it was too late.\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:18:18,054 --> 00:18:23,185\r\nDean, take Delacroix to the infirmary,\r\nsee if those fingers are broken.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:18:23,393 --> 00:18:25,953\r\nOf course they're broken.\r\nI heard the bones crack.\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:18:26,162 --> 00:18:28,960\r\nYou hear what he was yelling\r\nwhen we brought the dummy in?\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:18:29,165 --> 00:18:31,190\r\nHow could I miss it?\r\nThe whole prison heard.\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:18:31,968 --> 00:18:33,230\r\nGoddamn Percy.\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:18:33,970 --> 00:18:36,905\r\nYou'll have to answer\r\nfor sending him off the Mile.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:18:37,573 --> 00:18:40,064\r\nI'll chew that food when I have to.\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:18:40,376 --> 00:18:44,745\r\nRight now I wanna hear about this new\r\ninmate. Aside from how big he is, okay?\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:18:45,348 --> 00:18:47,645\r\nMonstrous big. Damn.\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:18:47,849 --> 00:18:49,840\r\nOh, he seems meek enough.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:18:50,051 --> 00:18:51,814\r\nIs he retarded, you figure?\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:18:52,487 --> 00:18:54,921\r\nLooks like they sent us\r\nan imbecile to execute.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:18:55,123 --> 00:18:58,422\r\nImbecile or not,\r\nhe deserves to fry for what he done.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:19:01,997 --> 00:19:04,022\r\nMake your blood curdle.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:19:27,856 --> 00:19:31,985\r\n- What?! For God's sake, what?\r\n- The girls! The girls are gone!\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:35,661\r\nPapa! Papa, look! There's blood.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:19:40,034 --> 00:19:41,797\r\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:19:46,574 --> 00:19:51,068\r\nGoddamn it, woman! Get on that phone\r\nnow. You tell them we headed west.\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:19:51,278 --> 00:19:54,372\r\nYou mind what I'm saying!\r\nWe headed west!\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:19:54,582 --> 00:19:57,016\r\nCentral! Are you on the line?\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:19:57,218 --> 00:20:01,382\r\nOh, God, please.\r\nSomebody took my little girls.\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:20:12,867 --> 00:20:14,528\r\nKatie!\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:20:15,502 --> 00:20:17,060\r\nCora!\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:20:48,101 --> 00:20:49,625\r\nJesus.\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:20:50,603 --> 00:20:52,093\r\nJesus.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:21:02,948 --> 00:21:04,347\r\nI'll kill you!\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,781\r\nI'll kill you!\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:21:38,617 --> 00:21:40,244\r\nI couldn't help it.\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:21:41,286 --> 00:21:44,880\r\nI tried to take it back,\r\nbut it was too late.\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:21:48,492 --> 00:21:51,689\r\nBoy, you under arrest for murder.\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:21:53,731 --> 00:21:55,255\r\nI interrupt?\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:21:56,834 --> 00:21:59,496\r\nWell, I'm just about done.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:10,642\r\nHey...\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:22:11,215 --> 00:22:13,740\r\n...how's that pretty gal of yours?\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:22:14,685 --> 00:22:16,949\r\nMelinda's not so well, Paul.\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:22:17,688 --> 00:22:18,916\r\nNot so well at all.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:22:20,758 --> 00:22:22,123\r\nMore headaches?\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:22:22,727 --> 00:22:25,355\r\nGot laid up with another one yesterday.\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:22:25,997 --> 00:22:27,430\r\nWorst one yet.\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:22:28,132 --> 00:22:32,090\r\nI'll be taking her over to Vicksburg\r\nnext day or so for some tests.\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:22:33,069 --> 00:22:35,867\r\nHead x-rays and who knows what else.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:22:36,072 --> 00:22:38,836\r\nShe is scared to death.\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:22:40,910 --> 00:22:42,901\r\nTruth to tell, so am I.\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:22:44,147 --> 00:22:47,048\r\nIf it's something they can see\r\non the x-ray...\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:22:47,651 --> 00:22:49,482\r\n...maybe it's something they can fix.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:22:50,453 --> 00:22:52,045\r\nMaybe.\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:22:56,259 --> 00:22:57,920\r\nThis just came in.\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:22:58,128 --> 00:23:00,494\r\nDOE on Bitterbuck.\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:06,025\r\nYou didn't come all the way down here\r\nto hand me a DOE.\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:11,473\r\nI had an angry call from\r\nthe state capitol about 20 minutes ago.\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:23:11,641 --> 00:23:14,007\r\nIs it true you ordered Percy Wetmore\r\noff the block?\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:15,506\r\nIt is.\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:23:16,412 --> 00:23:19,939\r\nNow, I'm sure you had reason, Paul...\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:23,949\r\n...but like it or not, the wife\r\nof the governor has only one nephew...\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:23:24,153 --> 00:23:26,018\r\n...and his name is Percy Wetmore.\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:23:26,255 --> 00:23:28,155\r\nLittle Percy calls his aunt...\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:23:28,357 --> 00:23:31,849\r\n...and squeals like a schoolroom sissy.\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:23:33,429 --> 00:23:37,593\r\nHe also mention he assaulted a prisoner\r\nthis morning out of sheer petulance?\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,530\r\nBroke three fingers\r\non Eduard Delacroix's left hand.\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:23:40,769 --> 00:23:43,363\r\nI didn't hear that part.\r\nI'm sure she didn't either.\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:23:43,572 --> 00:23:45,472\r\nThe man is mean and careless\r\nand stupid...\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:23:45,674 --> 00:23:48,541\r\n...and that's a bad combination\r\nin a place like this.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:23:48,711 --> 00:23:51,236\r\nSooner or later, he'll get\r\nsomebody hurt or worse.\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:23:51,447 --> 00:23:52,778\r\nStick with it, Paul.\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:23:53,148 --> 00:23:54,740\r\nIt may not be much longer.\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:23:54,950 --> 00:23:59,511\r\nI have it on good authority that Percy\r\nhas an application in at Briar Ridge.\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:23:59,687 --> 00:24:02,247\r\nBriar Ridge? The mental hospital.\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:24:02,457 --> 00:24:03,788\r\nAdministration job.\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:24:04,158 --> 00:24:05,489\r\nBetter pay.\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:24:07,128 --> 00:24:09,187\r\nThen why is he still here?\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:24:11,132 --> 00:24:13,396\r\nHe could get that application\r\npushed through.\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:24:15,670 --> 00:24:18,901\r\nHell, with his connections, he could\r\nhave any state job he wants.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:24:19,707 --> 00:24:21,368\r\nYou know what I think?\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:24:23,478 --> 00:24:26,970\r\nI think he just wants\r\nto see one cook up close.\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:24:29,884 --> 00:24:33,911\r\nWell, he'll get his chance, then.\r\nWon't he?\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:24:34,822 --> 00:24:38,952\r\nMaybe then he'll be satisfied\r\nand move on. In the meantime...\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:24:39,494 --> 00:24:42,429\r\n...you'll keep the peace?\r\n- Of course.\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:24:43,831 --> 00:24:45,058\r\nOf course.\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:24:46,833 --> 00:24:48,095\r\nThank you, Paul.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:24:52,038 --> 00:24:53,596\r\nHal...\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:24:54,574 --> 00:24:56,667\r\n...you give Melinda my love, okay?\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:24:57,177 --> 00:25:01,409\r\nI'm sure that x-ray will turn out\r\nto be nothing at all.\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:25:02,783 --> 00:25:04,011\r\nYou bet.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:25:30,976 --> 00:25:32,443\r\nPaul.\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:25:32,611 --> 00:25:34,374\r\n- Hey, you.\r\n- Hey.\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:25:35,047 --> 00:25:36,446\r\nThe music too loud?\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:25:38,450 --> 00:25:42,113\r\nThere's just this empty spot in the bed\r\nwhere my husband usually sleeps.\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:25:44,723 --> 00:25:48,318\r\nHe said to tell you he's having\r\na little trouble with that tonight.\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:25:51,797 --> 00:25:53,958\r\nWorried about Melinda and Hal?\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:25:54,667 --> 00:25:57,135\r\nIs that what's got you up?\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:25:57,303 --> 00:25:59,328\r\nYeah, that...\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:26:00,673 --> 00:26:02,140\r\n...and things.\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:26:03,175 --> 00:26:04,665\r\nThings.\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:26:09,048 --> 00:26:12,279\r\nWe got a new inmate today.\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:26:12,952 --> 00:26:14,919\r\nSimple-minded fella.\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:26:16,354 --> 00:26:18,447\r\nDo I wanna know what he did?\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:26:19,591 --> 00:26:21,149\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:26:22,026 --> 00:26:24,517\r\nThings that happen in this world.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:26:25,797 --> 00:26:27,992\r\nIt's a wonder God allows it.\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:26:32,370 --> 00:26:34,270\r\nWhy don't you come to bed.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:26:35,106 --> 00:26:38,200\r\nI think I have something\r\nthat'll help you sleep.\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:26:39,611 --> 00:26:41,704\r\nYou can have all you want.\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:26:42,814 --> 00:26:45,339\r\nI still got something wrong\r\nwith my waterworks.\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:47,541\r\nI don't wanna pass it on to you.\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:26:47,886 --> 00:26:51,219\r\n- Have you seen Doc Bishop yet?\r\n- No.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:26:53,391 --> 00:26:55,621\r\nHe'll just want me to take sulfa tablets...\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:26:55,827 --> 00:26:58,294\r\n...and I'll spend the week\r\npuking in my office.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:26:58,495 --> 00:27:02,556\r\nIt will run its course all by itself.\r\nThank you very much for your concern.\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:27:05,469 --> 00:27:06,936\r\nPoor old guy.\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:27:21,585 --> 00:27:23,917\r\nPaul. Dean.\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:27:28,325 --> 00:27:29,656\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:27:34,398 --> 00:27:37,424\r\nI guess the legislature loosened up\r\nthe purse strings enough...\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:27:37,601 --> 00:27:39,091\r\n...to hire on a new guard.\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:27:47,843 --> 00:27:49,071\r\nLook again.\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:27:49,412 --> 00:27:50,777\r\nHe's right...\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,513\r\n...there.\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:28:01,424 --> 00:28:04,257\r\nIt ain't normal for a mouse\r\nto come up on people.\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:28:05,061 --> 00:28:07,359\r\n- Maybe it's rabid.\r\n- Oh, my Christ.\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:28:07,563 --> 00:28:10,361\r\n- Yeah, it could be.\r\n- Oh, the big mouse expert.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,729\r\nThe Mouse Man.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:28:13,469 --> 00:28:15,869\r\nYou see him foaming at the mouth,\r\nMouse Man?\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:28:16,072 --> 00:28:18,267\r\nI don't see its mouth at all.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:28:27,383 --> 00:28:31,716\r\n- Brutal, no. We'll be hip-deep in mice.\r\n- I just wanna see what he'll do.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:28:32,153 --> 00:28:34,280\r\nIn the interest of science, like.\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:29:14,728 --> 00:29:16,753\r\nHe's in the damn restraint room.\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:19,364\r\nHe's chewing the padding\r\nout of the walls...\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:29:19,566 --> 00:29:21,534\r\n...making himself a nice little nest.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:29:26,907 --> 00:29:28,374\r\nAll right.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:29:28,976 --> 00:29:31,206\r\nLet's go get the damn mouse.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:29:43,057 --> 00:29:44,524\r\nBoss.\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:29:44,691 --> 00:29:46,522\r\nSaw me a mouse go by.\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:29:47,061 --> 00:29:48,926\r\nCan't put anything over on you.\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:04,041\r\nJust watch your toes. Watch your toes.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:30:22,261 --> 00:30:24,092\r\nYou let him get past you.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:30:24,297 --> 00:30:26,731\r\nNo, I did not.\r\nI been here all the time.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:30:26,933 --> 00:30:28,764\r\nThen where the hell is he?\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:30:28,968 --> 00:30:30,458\r\nWell, I don't know.\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:30:32,939 --> 00:30:34,804\r\nThree grown men...\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:30:35,575 --> 00:30:38,135\r\n...outsmarted by a mouse.\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:30:40,646 --> 00:30:45,480\r\nWell, bright side is, all this commotion\r\nprobably scared him off for good.\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:30:46,251 --> 00:30:47,946\r\nYeah, yeah.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:50,987\r\nYeah, that's the last\r\nwe'll see of him.\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:31:42,139 --> 00:31:45,040\r\nYou little son of a bitch.\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:31:46,610 --> 00:31:48,544\r\nWell, I'll be damned.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:31:48,946 --> 00:31:53,610\r\nThere he is, big as Billy-be-frigged.\r\nI thought Brutal was pulling my leg.\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:31:54,552 --> 00:31:56,520\r\n- That's a goddamn mouse.\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:31:57,588 --> 00:32:00,682\r\nBrute said he was in here last night...\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:32:00,891 --> 00:32:02,483\r\n...begging for food.\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:05,155\r\nHe come right on up to the desk.\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:32:06,363 --> 00:32:08,126\r\nGive him some room, Percy.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:32:08,299 --> 00:32:10,529\r\n- See what he does.\r\n- All right.\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:32:21,778 --> 00:32:25,407\r\nHe's a brave little bastard.\r\nGotta give him that.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:32:53,910 --> 00:32:55,377\r\nGoddamn!\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:32:56,312 --> 00:32:58,973\r\nYou little scurvy! Damn!\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:32:59,147 --> 00:33:02,139\r\nPercy, are you crazy,\r\nyou little son of a bitch?!\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:33:02,584 --> 00:33:04,449\r\nI'm gonna kill you!\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:33:06,021 --> 00:33:09,252\r\n- I'm gonna take you out!\r\n- Percy! Percy!\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:33:09,424 --> 00:33:12,916\r\nYou little vermin!\r\nI'm gonna stomp your life out!\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:33:13,128 --> 00:33:15,153\r\n<i>It's just a little mouse, dumb merde.</i>\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:33:15,364 --> 00:33:17,127\r\nYou ugly little piece of sh...\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:33:18,367 --> 00:33:19,994\r\n- Are you listening to me?\r\n- Fuck!\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:33:20,235 --> 00:33:23,932\r\n- Percy!\r\n- I'm gonna rip your diseased head off...\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:33:24,139 --> 00:33:25,572\r\n...you little piece of shit!\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:33:26,508 --> 00:33:30,604\r\n- Get on out of there!\r\n- I want you to stop this!\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,613\r\n- Hey, boss!\r\n- Hey, captain, what's going on?\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:33:46,727 --> 00:33:48,854\r\nPercy met your mouse.\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:33:51,132 --> 00:33:55,728\r\nIt's in here somewhere. I'm gonna\r\nsquish the little son of a bitch.\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:33:58,105 --> 00:34:00,539\r\nPercy, we already tried that.\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:34:04,045 --> 00:34:05,478\r\nWhat'd you say?\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:07,170\r\nI said that we...\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:34:11,485 --> 00:34:14,147\r\nKnock yourself out.\r\nHope you nail the bastard.\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:34:15,523 --> 00:34:17,081\r\nOh, yeah.\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:34:28,935 --> 00:34:31,335\r\nGosh. He ain't in there, huh?\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:34:31,838 --> 00:34:34,671\r\nDon't that beat the mousy band?\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:34:37,377 --> 00:34:38,901\r\nPercy...\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:34:40,580 --> 00:34:42,844\r\n...you wanna think about\r\nwhat you were doing?\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:34:43,049 --> 00:34:46,678\r\nI was trying to get the mouse.\r\nAre you blind?\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:34:46,886 --> 00:34:50,378\r\nYou also scared the living crap\r\nout of me and Bill...\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:34:50,590 --> 00:34:52,217\r\n...not to mention the inmates.\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:34:52,492 --> 00:34:53,789\r\nSo what?\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:34:53,993 --> 00:34:57,520\r\nThey aren't in cradle school,\r\nin case you didn't notice.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:34:58,131 --> 00:35:00,156\r\nAlthough you treat them that way.\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:35:00,367 --> 00:35:03,530\r\nWe don't scare them\r\nany more than we have to, Percy.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:35:03,737 --> 00:35:07,673\r\n- They're under enough strain as it is.\r\n- Men under strain can snap.\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:35:08,274 --> 00:35:11,367\r\nHurt themselves and hurt others.\r\nThat's why our job is...\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:35:12,378 --> 00:35:13,811\r\n...talking...\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:35:14,546 --> 00:35:16,036\r\n...not yelling.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:35:16,815 --> 00:35:20,182\r\nYou'd do better to think of this place\r\nlike an intensive care ward.\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:35:20,686 --> 00:35:23,883\r\nI think of it as a bucket of piss\r\nto drown rats in.\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:35:24,456 --> 00:35:25,787\r\nThat's all.\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:35:26,725 --> 00:35:28,852\r\nAnybody doesn't like it?\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:35:29,061 --> 00:35:31,291\r\nYou can kiss my ass.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:35:32,564 --> 00:35:34,361\r\nDon't. Yeah, you try it. Go on.\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:35:34,566 --> 00:35:38,263\r\nTry it. You'll be on the bread lines\r\nbefore the week is out.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,062\r\nOkay, Brutal.\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:35:52,451 --> 00:35:54,817\r\nWe all know who your connections are.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:59,449\r\nYou ever threaten a man on this block\r\nagain, we all gonna have a go.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:35:59,757 --> 00:36:01,224\r\nJob be damned.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:36:03,795 --> 00:36:05,262\r\nYou done?\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:12,530\r\nGet all this shit back in the room.\r\nYou are cluttering up my Mile.\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:36:34,692 --> 00:36:36,125\r\nArlen...\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:36:36,294 --> 00:36:38,660\r\n...your daughter and her family\r\nare here.\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:36:45,101 --> 00:36:49,128\r\nLet's move. I want at least two\r\nrehearsals before he gets back.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:36:52,209 --> 00:36:54,643\r\nSitting down, sitting down!\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:36:54,845 --> 00:36:56,540\r\nRehearsing now. Everybody settle!\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:36:56,746 --> 00:36:58,680\r\nArlen Bitterbuck, step forward.\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:36:59,216 --> 00:37:02,481\r\nStepping forward, stepping forward,\r\nstepping forward.\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:37:02,686 --> 00:37:05,985\r\n- Is his head properly shaved?\r\n- Nope. It's all dandruffy, and it smells.\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:37:06,189 --> 00:37:09,215\r\nI will take that as a yes.\r\nLet's go, Arlen.\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:13,095\r\nWalking the Mile, walking the Mile...\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:37:13,330 --> 00:37:17,630\r\n...walking the Mile, walking the Mile,\r\nwalking the Mile...\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:37:17,801 --> 00:37:19,166\r\n...walking the Mile.\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:37:19,369 --> 00:37:22,429\r\nI'm getting to my knees.\r\nI'm praying, praying.\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:37:22,639 --> 00:37:25,369\r\nLord is my shepherd\r\nand so forth and so on.\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:37:25,574 --> 00:37:30,034\r\nI'm sorry for all the bad shit\r\nI've done and people I've tramped on.\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:37:30,246 --> 00:37:32,714\r\nAnd I hope they forgive me...\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:37:32,915 --> 00:37:35,679\r\n...and I'll never do it again,\r\nthat's for sure.\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:37:35,885 --> 00:37:39,753\r\nPaul, we're not gonna have some\r\nCherokee medicine man in here...\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:37:39,955 --> 00:37:41,923\r\n...hollering and shaking his dick,\r\nare we?\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:37:42,124 --> 00:37:44,684\r\n- Well, actually...\r\n- Still praying, still praying.\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:37:44,894 --> 00: