 01:00:28,864\r\nDidn't we? Didn't we, all of us,\r\nthink he was doped?\r\n\r\n609\r\n01:00:29,069 --> 01:00:30,798\r\nYou didn't ask?\r\n\r\n610\r\n01:00:32,105 --> 01:00:33,970\r\nWell, I guess that's not a mistake...\r\n\r\n611\r\n01:00:34,341 --> 01:00:37,571\r\n...you'll be needing to make again\r\nanytime soon, is it?\r\n\r\n612\r\n01:00:51,624 --> 01:00:55,253\r\nYou go get Dean and Harry looked at.\r\nMake sure they're all right.\r\n\r\n613\r\n01:00:55,695 --> 01:00:59,222\r\nPercy, you make the report\r\nto the warden for me.\r\n\r\n614\r\n01:00:59,432 --> 01:01:01,992\r\nSay the situation's under control.\r\nIt's not a story.\r\n\r\n615\r\n01:01:02,201 --> 01:01:04,863\r\nHe won't appreciate you\r\ndrawing out the suspense.\r\n\r\n616\r\n01:01:05,071 --> 01:01:07,301\r\nWhat about you?\r\nYou're about to collapse.\r\n\r\n617\r\n01:01:07,540 --> 01:01:10,873\r\nI've got the Mile\r\ntill you all come back.\r\n\r\n618\r\n01:01:11,644 --> 01:01:13,612\r\nGo on, now. Go.\r\n\r\n619\r\n01:01:21,286 --> 01:01:24,414\r\nCome on, boy.\r\nLet's get you looked at.\r\n\r\n620\r\n01:01:50,015 --> 01:01:53,451\r\nBoss, I needs to see you down here.\r\n\r\n621\r\n01:01:56,988 --> 01:02:00,219\r\nThis is not a good time, John Coffey...\r\n\r\n622\r\n01:02:00,425 --> 01:02:02,393\r\n...not a good time at all.\r\n\r\n623\r\n01:02:02,594 --> 01:02:06,723\r\nBut I needs to see you, boss.\r\nI needs to talk to you.\r\n\r\n624\r\n01:02:28,786 --> 01:02:30,083\r\nCloser.\r\n\r\n625\r\n01:02:30,621 --> 01:02:32,680\r\nBoss, you know you ain't\r\nsupposed to do that.\r\n\r\n626\r\n01:02:34,325 --> 01:02:36,293\r\nMind your business, Del.\r\n\r\n627\r\n01:02:45,936 --> 01:02:47,961\r\nWhat do you want, John Coffey?\r\n\r\n628\r\n01:02:49,038 --> 01:02:50,130\r\nJust to help it.\r\n\r\n629\r\n01:02:53,810 --> 01:02:55,243\r\nDon't be afraid.\r\n\r\n630\r\n01:02:55,812 --> 01:02:56,836\r\nHelp!\r\n\r\n631\r\n01:02:57,647 --> 01:03:00,445\r\nHelp! John Coffey's\r\nkilling Boss Edgecomb!\r\n\r\n632\r\n01:03:00,616 --> 01:03:02,140\r\nHelp!\r\n\r\n633\r\n01:03:02,352 --> 01:03:05,583\r\n- What are you doing?\r\n- Help!\r\n\r\n634\r\n01:03:08,157 --> 01:03:10,022\r\nBoss Howell! Help!\r\n\r\n635\r\n01:03:10,727 --> 01:03:12,456\r\nBoss Stanton! Somebody, come!\r\n\r\n636\r\n01:03:12,795 --> 01:03:14,763\r\nHelp!\r\n\r\n637\r\n01:03:31,180 --> 01:03:33,410\r\nHelp! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!\r\n\r\n638\r\n01:03:33,616 --> 01:03:36,584\r\nSomebody, come!\r\nJohn Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!\r\n\r\n639\r\n01:03:36,785 --> 01:03:39,413\r\nDel, for chrissakes, shut up!\r\n\r\n640\r\n01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:28,230\r\nWhat did you just do to me?\r\n\r\n641\r\n01:04:30,204 --> 01:04:31,899\r\nI helped it.\r\n\r\n642\r\n01:04:32,973 --> 01:04:34,600\r\nDidn't I help it?\r\n\r\n643\r\n01:04:35,709 --> 01:04:37,939\r\nI just took it back, is all.\r\n\r\n644\r\n01:04:38,746 --> 01:04:41,214\r\nAwful tired now, boss.\r\n\r\n645\r\n01:04:41,749 --> 01:04:43,444\r\nDog-tired.\r\n\r\n646\r\n01:05:07,574 --> 01:05:10,600\r\nBoss, what that man do to you?\r\n\r\n647\r\n01:06:13,071 --> 01:06:15,835\r\nHey, honey. How you feeling?\r\n\r\n648\r\n01:06:17,643 --> 01:06:20,407\r\nOh, not too bad.\r\n\r\n649\r\n01:06:21,647 --> 01:06:23,410\r\nWhat did the doctor say?\r\n\r\n650\r\n01:06:25,651 --> 01:06:27,380\r\nOh, you know doctors.\r\n\r\n651\r\n01:06:27,819 --> 01:06:29,719\r\nGobbledygook, mostly.\r\n\r\n652\r\n01:06:30,822 --> 01:06:32,187\r\nGobbledygook.\r\n\r\n653\r\n01:06:47,438 --> 01:06:49,030\r\nHaving stew tonight.\r\n\r\n654\r\n01:06:59,350 --> 01:07:01,045\r\nWhat are you doing?\r\n\r\n655\r\n01:07:07,758 --> 01:07:09,623\r\nWhat does it feel like?\r\n\r\n656\r\n01:07:10,494 --> 01:07:12,928\r\nWell, I know what it feels like.\r\n\r\n657\r\n01:07:16,567 --> 01:07:18,466\r\nIt feels great.\r\n\r\n658\r\n01:07:52,897 --> 01:07:54,797\r\n- Paul.\r\n- Yeah?\r\n\r\n659\r\n01:07:55,232 --> 01:07:57,962\r\nNot that I'm complaining...\r\n\r\n660\r\n01:07:59,103 --> 01:08:02,833\r\n...but we haven't gone four times\r\nin one night since we were 19.\r\n\r\n661\r\n01:08:03,073 --> 01:08:05,439\r\nYeah, we did, at your mom's.\r\n\r\n662\r\n01:08:06,943 --> 01:08:08,934\r\nWanna tell me what's going on?\r\n\r\n663\r\n01:08:12,749 --> 01:08:14,114\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n664\r\n01:08:15,418 --> 01:08:17,409\r\n...see, the thing is...\r\n\r\n665\r\n01:08:18,621 --> 01:08:22,182\r\n...I never actually made it in\r\nto Dr. Bishop's yesterday.\r\n\r\n666\r\n01:08:25,362 --> 01:08:28,160\r\nBrutal, Paul. Listen.\r\n\r\n667\r\n01:08:28,365 --> 01:08:32,802\r\nI'm thinking of taking the morning\r\noff sick. You cover the fort for me?\r\n\r\n668\r\n01:08:33,870 --> 01:08:36,134\r\nThat's swell. Thanks.\r\n\r\n669\r\n01:08:36,339 --> 01:08:38,967\r\nYeah, no, I'm sure I'll feel better.\r\n\r\n670\r\n01:08:39,209 --> 01:08:41,837\r\nOkay. Okay.\r\n\r\n671\r\n01:08:47,217 --> 01:08:49,184\r\nYou're sure you ought to do this?\r\n\r\n672\r\n01:08:50,786 --> 01:08:53,016\r\nI'm not sure what I'm sure of.\r\n\r\n673\r\n01:09:09,838 --> 01:09:12,830\r\nBurt, you got some company.\r\n\r\n674\r\n01:09:13,509 --> 01:09:15,101\r\nCan I offer you a cold drink?\r\n\r\n675\r\n01:09:15,344 --> 01:09:18,438\r\nOh, yes, ma'am. A cold drink\r\nwould be fine. Thank you.\r\n\r\n676\r\n01:09:18,781 --> 01:09:21,875\r\nMr. Hammersmith, your office said\r\nI might find you at home.\r\n\r\n677\r\n01:09:22,084 --> 01:09:23,745\r\nHope I'm not troubling you.\r\n\r\n678\r\n01:09:24,420 --> 01:09:26,513\r\nWell, that depends, Mr?\r\n\r\n679\r\n01:09:26,722 --> 01:09:30,749\r\nPaul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor\r\nup on Cold Mountain.\r\n\r\n680\r\n01:09:31,960 --> 01:09:33,324\r\nThe Green Mile.\r\n\r\n681\r\n01:09:33,528 --> 01:09:36,656\r\nYeah, I've heard of it.\r\nLost a few clients your way.\r\n\r\n682\r\n01:09:37,432 --> 01:09:40,026\r\nI'd like to ask you about one of them.\r\n\r\n683\r\n01:09:41,302 --> 01:09:43,293\r\n- Have a seat.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n684\r\n01:09:48,042 --> 01:09:49,805\r\nWhich client?\r\n\r\n685\r\n01:09:51,279 --> 01:09:54,077\r\nNow you got my curiosity aroused.\r\n\r\n686\r\n01:09:54,282 --> 01:09:55,613\r\nJohn Coffey.\r\n\r\n687\r\n01:09:56,818 --> 01:09:58,217\r\nCoffey.\r\n\r\n688\r\n01:09:58,386 --> 01:09:59,614\r\nHe causing you problems?\r\n\r\n689\r\n01:10:00,088 --> 01:10:03,649\r\nNo. Can't say he is. He doesn't like\r\nthe dark and cries on occasion...\r\n\r\n690\r\n01:10:03,858 --> 01:10:05,723\r\n...but other than that...\r\n\r\n691\r\n01:10:05,893 --> 01:10:09,192\r\nHe cries, does he?\r\nWell, got a lot to cry about, I'd say.\r\n\r\n692\r\n01:10:09,397 --> 01:10:10,955\r\nYou know what he did.\r\n\r\n693\r\n01:10:11,632 --> 01:10:13,657\r\nI read the court transcript.\r\n\r\n694\r\n01:10:14,569 --> 01:10:17,332\r\n- Thank you, missus.\r\n- My pleasure.\r\n\r\n695\r\n01:10:18,205 --> 01:10:21,504\r\nKids! Lunch is about ready.\r\nY'all come on up.\r\n\r\n696\r\n01:10:21,741 --> 01:10:23,038\r\n- Coming, Mama!\r\n- Coming, Mama!\r\n\r\n697\r\n01:10:23,243 --> 01:10:26,371\r\nWhat exactly are you\r\ntrying to find out?\r\n\r\n698\r\n01:10:26,980 --> 01:10:29,312\r\nI've wondered if he did anything\r\nlike that before.\r\n\r\n699\r\n01:10:30,784 --> 01:10:32,752\r\nWhy? Has he said anything?\r\n\r\n700\r\n01:10:32,953 --> 01:10:36,116\r\nNo, but a man who does\r\na thing like that...\r\n\r\n701\r\n01:10:36,323 --> 01:10:40,225\r\n...has often developed a taste for it\r\nover time. It occurred to me...\r\n\r\n702\r\n01:10:40,427 --> 01:10:44,329\r\n...that it might be easy enough\r\nto follow his back trail. Find out.\r\n\r\n703\r\n01:10:45,098 --> 01:10:48,898\r\nA man his size, and colored to boot,\r\ncan't be that hard to trace.\r\n\r\n704\r\n01:10:49,102 --> 01:10:52,094\r\nYou'd think so, but you'd be wrong.\r\n\r\n705\r\n01:10:52,305 --> 01:10:54,432\r\nBelieve me, we tried.\r\n\r\n706\r\n01:10:55,275 --> 01:10:57,470\r\nLike he'd dropped out of the sky.\r\n\r\n707\r\n01:10:58,278 --> 01:10:59,711\r\nHow can that be?\r\n\r\n708\r\n01:10:59,946 --> 01:11:04,143\r\nWe're in a depression.\r\nA third of the country's out of work.\r\n\r\n709\r\n01:11:04,350 --> 01:11:08,377\r\nPeople are drifting by the thousands,\r\nlooking for jobs, for greener grass.\r\n\r\n710\r\n01:11:08,621 --> 01:11:11,749\r\nEven a giant like Coffey\r\nwouldn't get noticed everywhere.\r\n\r\n711\r\n01:11:12,525 --> 01:11:14,857\r\nNot until he kills\r\na couple of little girls.\r\n\r\n712\r\n01:11:15,694 --> 01:11:17,286\r\nHe is...\r\n\r\n713\r\n01:11:17,630 --> 01:11:19,689\r\n...strange, I admit.\r\n\r\n714\r\n01:11:20,065 --> 01:11:24,365\r\nBut there doesn't seem to be\r\nany real violence in him.\r\n\r\n715\r\n01:11:24,803 --> 01:11:27,237\r\nI know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.\r\n\r\n716\r\n01:11:27,473 --> 01:11:30,306\r\nI deal with them day in and day out.\r\n\r\n717\r\n01:11:31,110 --> 01:11:33,772\r\nYou didn't come to ask me\r\nwhether he killed before.\r\n\r\n718\r\n01:11:33,979 --> 01:11:36,914\r\nYou came to see if I think\r\nhe did it at all.\r\n\r\n719\r\n01:11:38,317 --> 01:11:40,012\r\nDo you?\r\n\r\n720\r\n01:11:41,220 --> 01:11:43,381\r\nOne seldom sees a less ambiguous case.\r\n\r\n721\r\n01:11:43,589 --> 01:11:45,648\r\nHe was found with the victims\r\nin his arms.\r\n\r\n722\r\n01:11:45,858 --> 01:11:47,654\r\nAnd yet you defended him.\r\n\r\n723\r\n01:11:48,660 --> 01:11:51,254\r\nEveryone is entitled to a defense.\r\n\r\n724\r\n01:11:51,663 --> 01:11:53,290\r\nKids! Lunch!\r\n\r\n725\r\n01:11:53,498 --> 01:11:54,795\r\nY'all listen to your mama!\r\n\r\n726\r\n01:11:59,437 --> 01:12:00,995\r\nI'll tell you something.\r\n\r\n727\r\n01:12:02,073 --> 01:12:05,668\r\nAnd you listen close too, because it\r\nmight be something you need to know.\r\n\r\n728\r\n01:12:05,877 --> 01:12:07,242\r\nI'm listening.\r\n\r\n729\r\n01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,614\r\nWe had us a dog.\r\n\r\n730\r\n01:12:10,782 --> 01:12:12,807\r\nJust a sweet mongrel.\r\n\r\n731\r\n01:12:13,017 --> 01:12:14,507\r\nYou know the kind.\r\n\r\n732\r\n01:12:15,887 --> 01:12:19,323\r\nWell, in many ways,\r\na good mongrel dog is like a Negro.\r\n\r\n733\r\n01:12:20,191 --> 01:12:21,954\r\nYou get to know it.\r\n\r\n734\r\n01:12:22,160 --> 01:12:26,529\r\nOften, you get to love it.\r\nIt is of no particular use...\r\n\r\n735\r\n01:12:26,731 --> 01:12:30,258\r\n...but you keep it around\r\nbecause you think it loves you.\r\n\r\n736\r\n01:12:31,768 --> 01:12:35,898\r\nIf you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you\r\nnever have to find out any different.\r\n\r\n737\r\n01:12:36,974 --> 01:12:39,169\r\nMy wife and I were not so lucky.\r\n\r\n738\r\n01:12:41,144 --> 01:12:42,668\r\nCaleb, come here for a second.\r\n\r\n739\r\n01:12:44,081 --> 01:12:45,275\r\nCome here.\r\n\r\n740\r\n01:12:46,717 --> 01:12:47,979\r\nPlease, son.\r\n\r\n741\r\n01:12:49,586 --> 01:12:52,054\r\nHe still has the one good eye.\r\n\r\n742\r\n01:12:53,423 --> 01:12:55,687\r\nI suppose he's lucky...\r\n\r\n743\r\n01:12:55,892 --> 01:12:58,258\r\n...not to be completely blind.\r\n\r\n744\r\n01:13:00,964 --> 01:13:04,730\r\nWe get down on our knees and thank God\r\nfor that much at least.\r\n\r\n745\r\n01:13:05,402 --> 01:13:06,801\r\nRight, Caleb?\r\n\r\n746\r\n01:13:09,273 --> 01:13:10,570\r\nOkay, go on in now.\r\n\r\n747\r\n01:13:14,011 --> 01:13:16,945\r\nThat dog attacked my boy\r\nfor no reason.\r\n\r\n748\r\n01:13:17,546 --> 01:13:19,741\r\nJust got it in his mind one day.\r\n\r\n749\r\n01:13:20,516 --> 01:13:21,983\r\nThe same with John Coffey.\r\n\r\n750\r\n01:13:22,184 --> 01:13:26,416\r\nHe was sorry afterwards.\r\nOf that I have no doubt.\r\n\r\n751\r\n01:13:27,089 --> 01:13:28,954\r\nBut those little girls...\r\n\r\n752\r\n01:13:29,158 --> 01:13:31,592\r\n...stayed raped and murdered.\r\n\r\n753\r\n01:13:32,261 --> 01:13:34,252\r\nMaybe he'd never done it before.\r\n\r\n754\r\n01:13:36,032 --> 01:13:38,193\r\nMy dog never bit before.\r\n\r\n755\r\n01:13:39,935 --> 01:13:42,665\r\nBut I didn't concern myself with that.\r\n\r\n756\r\n01:13:43,673 --> 01:13:47,632\r\nI went out with my rifle, grabbed\r\nhis collar and blew his brains out.\r\n\r\n757\r\n01:13:49,011 --> 01:13:50,171\r\nIs Coffey guilty?\r\n\r\n758\r\n01:13:53,115 --> 01:13:54,844\r\nYes, he is.\r\n\r\n759\r\n01:13:55,451 --> 01:13:57,112\r\nDon't you doubt it.\r\n\r\n760\r\n01:13:57,486 --> 01:13:59,954\r\nAnd don't you turn your back on him.\r\n\r\n761\r\n01:14:00,790 --> 01:14:04,953\r\nYou may get away with it once\r\nor even a hundred times...\r\n\r\n762\r\n01:14:05,794 --> 01:14:07,455\r\n...but in the end...\r\n\r\n763\r\n01:14:09,464 --> 01:14:10,931\r\n...you'll get bit.\r\n\r\n764\r\n01:14:23,511 --> 01:14:26,036\r\nOh, me! Oh, my!\r\n\r\n765\r\n01:14:28,383 --> 01:14:31,318\r\nJohn. John.\r\n\r\n766\r\n01:14:32,887 --> 01:14:35,117\r\nI'm smelling me some corn bread.\r\n\r\n767\r\n01:14:35,557 --> 01:14:37,457\r\nIt's from my missus.\r\n\r\n768\r\n01:14:41,162 --> 01:14:43,528\r\nShe wanted to thank you.\r\n\r\n769\r\n01:14:44,899 --> 01:14:46,297\r\nThank me for what?\r\n\r\n770\r\n01:14:46,734 --> 01:14:47,996\r\nWell, you know.\r\n\r\n771\r\n01:14:50,738 --> 01:14:52,137\r\nFor helping me.\r\n\r\n772\r\n01:14:52,840 --> 01:14:54,398\r\nHelping you with what?\r\n\r\n773\r\n01:14:55,109 --> 01:14:56,235\r\nYou know.\r\n\r\n774\r\n01:15:02,783 --> 01:15:04,751\r\nWas your missus pleased?\r\n\r\n775\r\n01:15:06,587 --> 01:15:08,248\r\nSeveral times.\r\n\r\n776\r\n01:15:23,771 --> 01:15:27,263\r\nOh, John, I can smell that\r\nfrom over here. I surely can.\r\n\r\n777\r\n01:15:30,144 --> 01:15:32,441\r\nCan I give Del and Mr. Jingles some?\r\n\r\n778\r\n01:15:33,045 --> 01:15:36,606\r\nWell, it's yours, John.\r\nYou can do with it as you please.\r\n\r\n779\r\n01:15:39,652 --> 01:15:43,144\r\nHere. This for Del and Mr. Jingles.\r\n\r\n780\r\n01:15:43,890 --> 01:15:47,553\r\nHey! What about me?\r\nI'm gonna get some too, ain't I?\r\n\r\n781\r\n01:15:49,662 --> 01:15:52,